  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Introduction'
      title: Introduction
      number: 1
      content: '  The first account I made, Theophilus, was [a continuous report]
        about all the things that Jesus began to do and to teach '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'until the day when He ascended to heaven, after He had by the Holy
        Spirit given instruction to the apostles (special messengers) whom He had
        chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'To these [men] He also showed Himself alive after His suffering [in
        Gethsemane and on the cross], by [a series of] many infallible proofs and
        unquestionable demonstrations, appearing to them over a period of forty days
        and talking to them about the things concerning the kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "While being together and eating with them, He commanded them not
        to leave Jerusalem, but to wait for what the Father had promised, <JESUS>\u201COf
        which,\u201D</JESUS>  He said,  <JESUS>\u201Cyou have heard Me speak.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>For John baptized with water, but you will be baptized </JESUS>and
        empowered and united with the Holy Spirit, not long from now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So when they had come together, they asked Him repeatedly, \u201CLord,
        are You at this time reestablishing the kingdom and restoring it to Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIt is not for you to know the times
        or epochs which the Father has fixed by His own authority.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Ascension'
      title: The Ascension
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>But you will receive power </JESUS>and ability when the Holy
        Spirit comes upon you; and you will be My witnesses [to tell people about
        Me] <JESUS>both in Jerusalem and in all Judea, and Samaria, and even to the
        ends of the earth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And after He said these things, He was caught up as they looked on,
        and a cloud took Him up out of their sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'While they were looking intently into the sky as He was going, two
        men in white clothing suddenly stood beside them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Upper Room'
      title: The Upper Room
      number: 11
      content: "who said, \u201CMen of Galilee, why do you stand looking into the
        sky? This [same] Jesus, who has been taken up from you into heaven, will
        return in just the same way as you have watched Him go into heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the disciples returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet
        (Olive Grove), which is near Jerusalem, [only] a Sabbath day\u2019s journey
        (less than one mile) away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When they had entered the city, they went upstairs to the upper room
        where they were staying [indefinitely]; that is, Peter, and John and [his
        brother] James, and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew (Nathanael) and
        Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon the Zealot, and Judas (Thaddaeus)
        the son of James. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'All these with one mind and one purpose were continually devoting
        themselves to prayer, [waiting together] along with the women, and Mary the
        mother of Jesus, and with His brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now on one of these days Peter stood up among the brothers and sisters
        (a gathering of about a hundred and twenty believers was there) and he said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBrothers and sisters, it was necessary that the Scripture be
        fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit foretold by the lips of David [king of Israel]
        about Judas [Iscariot], who acted as guide to those who arrested Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For he (Judas) was counted among us and received his share [by divine
        allotment] in this ministry.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(Now Judas Iscariot acquired a piece of land [indirectly] with the
        [money paid him as a] reward for his treachery, and falling headlong, his
        body burst open in the middle and all his intestines poured out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "All the people in Jerusalem learned about this, so in their own dialect\u2014Aramaic\u2014they
        called the piece of land Hakeldama, that is, Field of Blood.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor in the book of Psalms it is written,\u2018Let his place
        of residence become desolate,And let there be no one to live in it\u2019;and
        [again],\u2018Let another take his position as overseer.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So of the men who have accompanied us during all the time that the
        Lord Jesus spent with us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "beginning with the baptism by John [at the outset of Jesus\u2019
        ministry] until the day when He was taken up from us\u2014one of these men
        must become a witness with us [to testify] of His resurrection.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they put forward two men, Joseph, the one called Barsabbas (who
        was surnamed Justus), and Matthias. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They prayed and said, \u201CYou, Lord, who know all hearts [their
        thoughts, motives, desires], show us which one of these two You have chosen "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "to occupy this ministry and apostleship which Judas left to go to
        his own place [of evil].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And they cast lots for them, and the lot fell to Matthias; and he
        was added to the eleven apostles.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Day of Pentecost'
      title: The Day of Pentecost
      number: 1
      content: '  When the day of Pentecost had come, they were all together in one
        place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and suddenly a sound came from heaven like a rushing violent wind,
        and it filled the whole house where they were sitting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'There appeared to them tongues resembling fire, which were being
        distributed [among them], and they rested on each one of them [as each person
        received the Holy Spirit]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they were all filled [that is, diffused throughout their being]
        with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues (different languages),
        as the Spirit was giving them the ability to speak out [clearly and appropriately].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now there were Jews living in Jerusalem, devout and God-fearing men
        from every nation under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when this sound was heard, a crowd gathered, and they were bewildered
        because each one was hearing those in the upper room speaking in his own
        language or dialect. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They were completely astonished, saying, \u201CLook! Are not all
        of these who are speaking Galileans? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then how is it that each of us hears in our own language or native
        dialect? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '[Among us there are] Parthians, Medes and Elamites, and people of
        Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia [Minor], '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the districts of Libya around Cyrene,
        and the visitors from Rome, both Jews and proselytes (Gentile converts to
        Judaism), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Cretans and Arabs\u2014we all hear them speaking in our [native]
        tongues about the mighty works of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they were beside themselves with amazement and were greatly perplexed,
        saying one to another, \u201CWhat could this mean?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Peter\u2019s Sermon"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Sermon"
      number: 13
      content: "But others were laughing and joking and ridiculing them, saying,
        \u201CThey are full of sweet wine and are drunk!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter, standing with the eleven, raised his voice and addressed
        them: \u201CMen of Judea and all you who live in Jerusalem, let this be explained
        to you; listen closely and pay attention to what I have to say. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These people are not drunk, as you assume, since it is [only] the
        third hour of the day (9:00 a.m.); '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but this is [the beginning of] what was spoken of through the prophet
        Joel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018And it shall be in the last days,\u2019 says God,\u2018That
        I will pour out My Spirit upon all mankind;And your sons and your daughters
        shall prophesy,And your young men shall see [divinely prompted] visions,And
        your old men shall dream [divinely prompted] dreams;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Even on My bond-servants, both men and women,I will in those days
        pour out My SpiritAnd they shall prophesy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will bring about wonders in the sky aboveAnd signs (attesting
        miracles) on the earth below,Blood and fire and smoking vapor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sun shall be turned into darknessAnd the moon into blood,Before
        the great and glorious day of the Lord comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And it shall be that everyone who calls upon the name of the Lord
        [invoking, adoring, and worshiping the Lord Jesus] shall be saved (rescued
        spiritually).\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMen of Israel, listen to these words: Jesus of Nazareth, a
        Man accredited and pointed out and attested to you by God with [the power
        to perform] miracles and wonders and signs which God worked through Him in
        your [very] midst, just as you yourselves know\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'this Man, when handed over [to the Roman authorities] according to
        the predetermined decision and foreknowledge of God, you nailed to a cross
        and put to death by the hands of lawless and godless men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But God raised Him up, releasing Him and bringing an end to the agony
        of death, since it was impossible for Him to be held in death\u2019s power. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David says of Him,\u2018I saw the Lord constantly before me;For
        He is at my right hand, so that I will not be shaken [from my state of security].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore my heart rejoiced and my tongue exulted exceedingly;Moreover
        my flesh also will live in hope [that is, will encamp in anticipation of
        the resurrection];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For You will not forsake me  and  abandon my soul to Hades (the realm
        of the dead),Nor let Your Holy One undergo decay [after death].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You have made known to me the ways of life;You will fill me [infusing
        my soul] with joy with Your presence.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CBrothers, I may confidently and freely say to you regarding
        the patriarch David that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with
        us to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And so, being a prophet and knowing fully that God had sworn to him
        with an oath that He would seat  one  of his descendants on his throne, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'he foresaw and spoke [prophetically] of the resurrection of the Christ
        (the Messiah, the Anointed), that He was not abandoned [in death] to Hades
        (the realm of the dead), nor did His body undergo decay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'God raised this Jesus [bodily from the dead], and of that [fact]
        we are all witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Therefore having been exalted to the right hand of God, and having
        received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, He has poured out
        this [blessing] which you both see and hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For David did not ascend into the heavens, yet he himself says,\u2018The
        Lord [the Father] said to my  Lord [the Son],\u201CSit at My right hand,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Until I make Your enemies a  footstool for Your feet.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: The Ingathering'
      title: The Ingathering
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore let all the house of Israel recognize beyond all doubt
        that God has made Him both Lord and Christ (Messiah, Anointed)\u2014this
        Jesus whom you crucified.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now when they heard this, they were cut to the heart [with remorse
        and anxiety], and they said to Peter and the rest of the apostles, \u201CBrothers,
        what are we to do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Peter said to them, \u201CRepent [change your old way of thinking,
        turn from your sinful ways, accept and follow Jesus as the Messiah] and be
        baptized, each of you, in the name of Jesus Christ because of the forgiveness
        of your sins; and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For the promise [of the Holy Spirit] is for you and your children
        and for all who are far away [including the Gentiles], as many as the Lord
        our God calls to Himself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And Peter solemnly testified and continued to admonish and urge them
        with many more words, saying, \u201CBe saved from this crooked and unjust
        generation!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'So then, those who accepted his message were baptized; and on that
        day about 3,000 souls were added [to the body of believers]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They were continually and faithfully devoting themselves to the instruction
        of the apostles, and to fellowship, to eating meals together and to prayers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'A sense of awe was felt by everyone, and many wonders and signs (attesting
        miracles) were taking place through the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And all those who had believed [in Jesus as Savior] were together
        and had all things in common [considering their possessions to belong to
        the group as a whole]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And they began selling their property and possessions and were sharing
        the proceeds with all [the other believers], as anyone had need. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Day after day they met in the temple [area] continuing with one mind,
        and breaking bread in various private homes. They were eating their meals
        together with joy and generous hearts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: praising God continually, and having favor with all the people. And
        the Lord kept adding to their number daily those who were being saved.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Healing the Lame Beggar'
      title: Healing the Lame Beggar
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Peter and John were going up to the temple at the hour of prayer,
        the ninth hour (3:00 p.m.), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and a man who had been unable to walk from birth was being carried
        along, whom they used to set down every day at that gate of the temple which
        is called Beautiful, so that he could beg alms from those entering the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So when he saw Peter and John about to go into the temple, he began
        asking [them] for coins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Peter, along with John, stared at him intently and said, \u201CLook
        at us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the man began to pay attention to them, eagerly expecting to
        receive something from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CSilver and gold I do not have; but what I do
        have I give to you: In the name (authority, power) of Jesus Christ the Nazarene\u2014[begin
        now to] walk and go on walking!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he seized the man\u2019s right hand with a firm grip and raised
        him up. And at once his feet and ankles became strong and steady, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and with a leap he stood up and began to walk; and he went into the
        temple with them, walking and leaping and praising God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All the people saw him walking and praising God; '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Peter\u2019s Second Sermon"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Second Sermon"
      number: 10
      content: 'and they recognized him as the very man who usually sat begging for
        coins at the Beautiful Gate of the temple, and they were filled with wonder
        and amazement and were mystified at what had happened to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now while he was still holding on to Peter and John, all the people,
        utterly amazed, ran together and crowded around them at the covered porch
        called Solomon\u2019s portico. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Peter, seeing this, said to the people, \u201CYou men of Israel,
        why are you amazed at this? Why are you staring at us, as though by our own
        power or godliness we had made this man walk? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, the God of our fathers, has
        glorified His Servant and Son Jesus [doing Him this honor], the One whom
        you handed over and disowned and rejected before Pilate, when he had decided
        to release Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But you disowned and denied the Holy and Righteous One and asked
        for [the pardon of] a murderer to be granted to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But you killed the Prince (Author, Originator, Source) of life, whom
        God raised [bodily] from the dead. To this [fact] we are witnesses [for we
        have seen the risen Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And on the basis of faith in His name, it is the name of Jesus which
        has strengthened this man whom you see and know; and the faith which comes
        through Him has given him this perfect health and complete wholeness in your
        presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CNow, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance [not fully
        aware of what you were doing], just as your rulers did also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And so God has fulfilled what He foretold by the mouth of all the
        prophets, that His Christ (Messiah, Anointed) would suffer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So repent [change your inner self\u2014your old way of thinking,
        regret past sins] and return [to God\u2014seek His purpose for your life],
        so that your sins may be wiped away [blotted out, completely erased], so
        that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord [restoring
        you like a cool wind on a hot day]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and that He may send [to you] Jesus, the Christ, who has been appointed
        for you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'whom heaven must keep until the time for the [complete] restoration
        of all things about which God promised through the mouth of His holy prophets
        from ancient time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Moses said, \u2018The Lord God will raise up for you a Prophet  like
        me from your countrymen; you shall listen to Him  and  obey everything He
        tells you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it will be that every person that does not listen to and heed
        that Prophet will be utterly destroyed from among the people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Indeed, all the prophets who have spoken, from Samuel and those who
        came after him, also announced these days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You are the sons (descendants) of the prophets and [heirs] of the
        covenant which God made with your fathers, saying to Abraham, \u2018And in
        your seed (descendant) all the families of the earth shall be blessed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "It was for you first of all that God raised up His Servant and Son
        [Jesus], and sent Him to bless you by turning every one of you from your
        wicked ways.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter and John Arrested'
      title: Peter and John Arrested
      number: 1
      content: '  And while Peter and John were talking to the people, the priests
        and the captain [who was in charge of the temple area and] of the temple
        guard and the Sadducees came up to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'being extremely disturbed and thoroughly annoyed because they were
        teaching the people and proclaiming in [the case of] Jesus the resurrection
        of the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they arrested them and put them in jail until the next day, because
        it was evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But many of those who heard the message [of salvation] believed [in
        Jesus and accepted Him as the Christ]. And the number of the men came to
        be about 5,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the next day, their magistrates and elders and scribes (Sanhedrin,
        Jewish High Court) were gathered together in Jerusalem; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Annas the high priest was there, and Caiaphas and John and Alexander,
        and all others who were of high-priestly descent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When they had put the men in front of them, they repeatedly asked,
        \u201CBy what sort of power, or in what name [that is, by what kind of authority],
        did you do this [healing]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Peter, filled with [the power of] the Holy Spirit, said to them,
        \u201CRulers and elders of the people [members of the Sanhedrin, the Jewish
        High Court], "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'if we are being put on trial today [to interrogate us] for a good
        deed done to [benefit] a disabled man, as to how this man has been restored
        to health, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "let it be known and clearly understood by all of you, and by all
        the people of Israel, that in the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, whom
        you [demanded be] crucified [by the Romans and], whom God raised from the
        dead\u2014in this name [that is, by the authority and power of Jesus] this
        man stands here before you in good health. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This Jesus is the stone which was despised  and  rejected by you,
        the builders, but  which became the  chief Cornerstone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Threat and Release'
      title: Threat and Release
      number: 12
      content: "And there is salvation in no one else; for there is no other name
        under heaven that has been given among people by which we must be saved [for
        God has provided the world no alternative for salvation].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when the men of the Sanhedrin (Jewish High Court) saw the confidence
        and boldness of Peter and John, and grasped the fact that they were uneducated
        and untrained [ordinary] men, they were astounded, and began to recognize
        that they had been with Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And seeing the man who had been healed standing there with them,
        they had nothing to say in reply. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But after ordering them to step out of the Council [chamber], they
        began to confer among themselves, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "saying, \u201CWhat are we to do with these men? For the fact that
        an extraordinary miracle has taken place through them is public knowledge
        and clearly evident to all the residents of Jerusalem, and we cannot deny
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But to keep it from spreading further among the people and the nation,
        let us [sternly] warn them not to speak again to anyone in this name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So they sent for them, and commanded them not to speak [as His representatives]
        or teach at all in the name of Jesus [using Him as their authority]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Peter and John replied to them, \u201CWhether it is right in
        the sight of God to listen to you and obey you rather than God, you must
        judge [for yourselves]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "for we, on our part, cannot stop telling [people] about what we have
        seen and heard.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When the rulers and Council members had threatened them further,
        they let them go, finding no way to punish them because [of their fear] of
        the people, for they were all praising and glorifying and honoring God for
        what had happened; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'for the man to whom this sign (attesting miracle) of healing had
        happened was more than forty years old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After Peter and John were released, they returned to their own [people]
        and reported everything that the chief priests and elders had said to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when they heard it, they raised their voices together to God
        and said, \u201CO Sovereign Lord [having complete power and authority], it
        is You who made the heaven and the earth and the sea, and everything that
        is in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "who by the Holy Spirit, through the mouth of our father David, Your
        servant, said,\u2018Why did the nations (Gentiles) become arrogant  and 
        rage,And the peoples devise futile things [against the Lord]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The kings of the earth took their stand [to attack],And the rulers
        were assembled togetherAgainst the Lord and against His Anointed (the Christ,
        the Messiah).\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For in this city there were gathered together against Your holy Servant
        Jesus, whom You anointed, both Herod and Pontius Pilate, along with the Gentiles
        and the peoples of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'to do whatever Your hand and Your purpose predestined [before the
        creation of the world] to occur [and so without knowing it, they served Your
        own purpose]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And now, Lord, observe their threats [take them into account] and
        grant that Your bond-servants may declare Your message [of salvation] with
        great confidence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "while You extend Your hand to heal, and signs and wonders (attesting
        miracles) take place through the name [and the authority and power] of Your
        holy Servant and Son Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Sharing among Believers'
      title: Sharing among Believers
      number: 31
      content: "And when they had prayed, the place where they were meeting together
        was shaken [a sign of God\u2019s presence]; and they were all filled with
        the Holy Spirit and began to speak the word of God with boldness and courage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the company of believers was of one heart and soul, and not one
        [of them] claimed that anything belonging to him was [exclusively] his own,
        but everything was common property and for the use of all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And with great ability and power the apostles were continuously testifying
        to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and great grace [God\u2019s remarkable
        lovingkindness and favor and goodwill] rested richly upon them all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'There was not a needy person among them, because those who were owners
        of land or houses were selling them, and bringing the proceeds of the sales '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and placing the money down at the apostles\u2019 feet. Then it was
        distributed to each as anyone had need.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now Joseph, a Levite and native of Cyprus, who was surnamed Barnabas
        by the apostles (which translated means Son of Encouragement), '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "sold a field belonging to him and brought the money and set it at
        the apostles\u2019 feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fate of Ananias and Sapphira'
      title: Fate of Ananias and Sapphira
      number: 1
      content: '  Now a man named Ananias, with his wife Sapphira, sold a piece of
        property, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and with his wife\u2019s full knowledge [and complicity] he kept
        back some of the proceeds, bringing only a portion of it, and set it at the
        apostles\u2019 feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CAnanias, why has Satan filled your heart to
        lie to the Holy Spirit and [secretly] keep back for yourself some of the
        proceeds [from the sale] of the land? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "As long as it remained [unsold], did it not remain your own [to do
        with as you pleased]? And after it was sold, was the money not under your
        control? Why is it that you have conceived this act [of hypocrisy and deceit]
        in your heart? You have not [simply] lied to people, but to God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And hearing these words, Ananias fell down suddenly and died; and
        great fear and awe gripped those who heard of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the young men [in the congregation] got up and wrapped up the
        body, and carried it out and buried it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now after an interval of about three hours his wife came in, not
        knowing what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Peter asked her, \u201CTell me whether you sold your land for so
        much?\u201D And she said, \u201CYes, for so much.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Peter said to her, \u201CHow could you two have agreed together
        to put the Spirit of the Lord to the test? Look! The feet of those who have
        buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And at once she fell down at his feet and died; and the young men
        came in and found her dead, and they carried her out and buried her beside
        her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And great fear and awe gripped the whole church, and all who heard
        about these things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "At the hands of the apostles many signs and wonders (attesting miracles)
        were continually taking place among the people. And by common consent they
        all met together [at the temple] in [the covered porch called] Solomon\u2019s
        portico. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But none of the rest [of the people, the non-believers] dared to
        associate with them; however, the people were holding them in high esteem
        and were speaking highly of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'More and more believers in the Lord, crowds of men and women, were
        constantly being added to their number,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'to such an extent that they even carried their sick out into the
        streets and put them on cots and sleeping pads, so that when Peter came by
        at least his shadow might fall on one of them [with healing power]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Imprisonment and Release'
      title: Imprisonment and Release
      number: 16
      content: 'And the people from the towns in the vicinity of Jerusalem were coming
        together, bringing the sick and those who were tormented by unclean spirits,
        and they were all being healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the high priest stood up, along with all his associates (that
        is, the sect of the Sadducees), and they were filled with jealousy and resentment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They arrested the apostles and put them in a public jail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But during the night an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors,
        and leading them out, he said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGo, stand and continue to tell the people in the temple [courtyards]
        the whole message of this Life [the eternal life revealed by Christ and found
        through faith in Him].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When they heard this, they went into the temple [courtyards] about
        daybreak and began teaching.  Now when the high priest and his associates
        arrived, they called together the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court),
        even all the council of elders of the sons of Israel, and sent word to the
        prison for the apostles to be brought [before them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But when the officers arrived, they did not find them in the prison;
        and they came back and reported, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWe found the prison securely locked and the guards standing
        at the doors, but when we opened [the doors], we found no one inside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now when the captain of the temple guard and the chief priests heard
        these things, they were greatly perplexed, wondering what would come of this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But someone came and told them, \u201CThe men whom you put in prison
        are standing [right here] in the temple [area], teaching the people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the captain went with the officers and brought them back, without
        hurting them (because they were afraid of the people, worried that they might
        be stoned).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So they brought them and presented them before the Council (Sanhedrin,
        Jewish High Court). The high priest questioned them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "saying, \u201CWe gave you strict orders not to continue teaching
        in this name, and yet you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching and you
        intend to bring this Man\u2019s blood on us [by accusing us as His murderers].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Peter and the apostles replied, \u201CWe must obey God rather
        than men [we have no other choice]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom you had put to death
        by hanging Him on a cross [and you are responsible]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'God exalted Him to His right hand as Prince and Savior and Deliverer,
        in order to grant repentance to Israel, and [to grant] forgiveness of sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: "32: Gamaliel\u2019s Counsel"
      title: "Gamaliel\u2019s Counsel"
      number: 32
      content: "And we are witnesses of these things; and so is the Holy Spirit,
        whom God has bestowed on those who obey Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now when they heard this, they were infuriated and they intended
        to kill the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But a Pharisee named Gamaliel, a teacher of the Law [of Moses], highly
        esteemed by all the people, stood up in the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High
        Court) and ordered that the men be taken outside for a little while. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then he said to the Council, \u201CMen of Israel, be careful in regard
        to what you propose to do to these men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For some time ago Theudas rose up, claiming to be somebody [of importance],
        and a group of about four hundred men allied themselves with him. But he
        was killed, and all who followed him were scattered and came to nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'After this man, Judas the Galilean rose up, [and led an uprising]
        during the time of the census, and drew people after him; he was also killed,
        and all his followers were scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So in the present case, I say to you, stay away from these men and
        let them alone, for if this plan or action is of men [merely human in origin],
        it will fail and be destroyed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "but if it is of God [and it appears that it is], you will not be
        able to stop them; or else you may even be found fighting against God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court) took his advice; and after
        summoning the apostles, they flogged them and ordered them not to speak in
        the name of Jesus, and released them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'So they left the Council, rejoicing that they had been considered
        worthy [dignified by indignity] to suffer shame for [the sake of] His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And every single day, in the temple [area] and in homes, they did
        not stop teaching and telling the good news of Jesus as the Christ (the Messiah,
        the Anointed).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Choosing of the Seven'
      title: Choosing of the Seven
      number: 1
      content: '  Now about this time, when the number of disciples was increasing,
        a complaint was made by the Hellenists (Greek-speaking Jews) against the
        [native] Hebrews, because their widows were being overlooked in the daily
        serving of food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the Twelve called the disciples together and said, \u201CIt is
        not appropriate for us to neglect [teaching] the word of God in order to
        serve tables and manage the distribution of food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, brothers, choose from among you seven men with good reputations
        [men of godly character and moral integrity], full of the Spirit and of wisdom,
        whom we may put in charge of this task. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But we will [continue to] devote ourselves [steadfastly] to prayer
        and to the ministry of the word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The suggestion pleased the whole congregation; and they selected
        Stephen, a man full of faith [in Christ Jesus], and [filled with and led
        by] the Holy Spirit, and Philip, Prochorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and
        Nicolas (Nikolaos), a proselyte (Gentile convert) from Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They brought these men before the apostles; and after praying, they
        laid their hands on them [to dedicate and commission them for this service].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the message of God kept on growing and spreading, and the number
        of disciples continued to increase greatly in Jerusalem; and a large number
        of the priests were becoming obedient to the faith [accepting Jesus as Messiah
        and acknowledging Him as the Source of eternal salvation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now Stephen, full of grace (divine blessing, favor) and power, was
        doing great wonders and signs (attesting miracles) among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'However, some men from what was called the Synagogue of the Freedmen
        (freed Jewish slaves), both Cyrenians and Alexandrians, and some from Cilicia
        and [the province of] Asia, rose up and questioned and argued with Stephen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But they were not able to successfully withstand and cope with the
        wisdom and the intelligence [and the power and inspiration] of the Spirit
        by whom he was speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then [to attack him another way] they secretly instructed men to
        say, \u201CWe have heard this man [Stephen] speak blasphemous (slanderous,
        sacrilegious, abusive) words against Moses and against God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they provoked and incited the people, as well as the elders and
        the scribes, and they came up to Stephen and seized him and brought him before
        the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court). '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They presented false witnesses who said, \u201CThis man never stops
        speaking against this holy place and the Law [of Moses]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "for we have heard him say that this Jesus the Nazarene will tear
        down this place and will change the traditions and customs which Moses handed
        down to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then all those who were sitting in the Council, stared [intently]
        at him, and they saw that Stephen\u2019s face was like the face of an angel."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Stephen\u2019s Defense"
      title: "Stephen\u2019s Defense"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the high priest asked [Stephen], \u201CAre these charges true?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he answered, \u201CBrothers and fathers, listen to me! The God
        of glory [the Shekinah, the radiance of God] appeared to our father Abraham
        when he was in Mesopotamia, before he lived in Haran, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and He said to him, \u2018Leave your country and your relatives,
        and come to the land that I will show you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he left the land of the Chaldeans and settled in Haran. And
        from there, after his father died, God sent him to this country in which
        you now live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But He did not give him inheritable property, not even enough ground
        to take a step on, yet He promised that He would give it to Him as a possession,
        and to his descendants after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And this is, in effect, what God spoke [to him]: That his descendants
        would be aliens (strangers) in a foreign land, and that they would be enslaved
        and mistreated for four hundred years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018And I will judge any nation to whom they will be in bondage,\u2019
        said God, \u2018and after that they will come out and serve Me [in worship]
        in this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God gave Abraham a covenant [a formal agreement to be strictly
        observed] of [which] circumcision [was the sign]; and so [under these circumstances]
        Abraham became the father of Isaac, and circumcised him on the eighth day;
        and Isaac [became the father] of Jacob, and Jacob [became the father] of
        the twelve patriarchs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe [ten elder] patriarchs, overwhelmed with jealousy, sold
        [their younger brother] Joseph into [slavery in] Egypt; but God was with
        him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and He rescued him from all his suffering, and gave him favor and
        wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he made Joseph governor
        over Egypt and over his entire household.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow a famine came over all Egypt and Canaan, bringing great
        distress and our fathers could not find food [for their households and livestock]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent our fathers
        there the first time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And on the second visit Joseph identified himself to his brothers,
        and Joseph\u2019s family and background were revealed to Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Joseph sent and invited Jacob his father and all his relatives
        to come to him, seventy-five persons in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Jacob (Israel) went down into Egypt, and there he died, as did
        our fathers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and [from Egypt] their bodies were taken back to Shechem and placed
        in the tomb which Abraham had purchased for a sum of money from the sons
        of Hamor in Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut as the time [for the fulfillment] of the promise which
        God had made to Abraham was approaching, the [Hebrew] people increased and
        multiplied in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'until [the time when] there arose another king over egypt who did
        not know joseph [nor his history and the merit of his service to Egypt]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He shrewdly exploited our race and mistreated our fathers, forcing
        them to expose their [male] babies so that they would die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "It was at this [critical] time that Moses was born; and he was lovely
        in the sight of God, and for three months he was nourished in his father\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then when he was set outside [to die], Pharaoh\u2019s daughter rescued
        him and claimed him for herself, and cared for him as her own son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses was educated in all the wisdom and culture of the Egyptians,
        and he was a man of power in words and deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But when he reached the age of forty, it came into his heart to visit
        his brothers, the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when he saw one [of them] being treated unfairly, he defended
        the oppressed man and avenged him by striking and killing the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He expected his countrymen to understand that God was granting them
        freedom through him [assuming that they would accept him], but they did not
        understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then on the next day he suddenly appeared to two of them as they
        were fighting, and he tried to reconcile them, saying, \u2018Men, you are
        brothers; why do you wrong one another?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the man who was injuring his neighbor pushed Moses away, saying,
        \u2018Who appointed you ruler and judge over us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do you intend to kill me as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At this remark Moses fled and became an exile in the land of Midian,
        where he fathered two sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAfter forty years had passed, an angel appeared to him in the
        wilderness of Mount  Sinai, in the flame of a burning thorn bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When Moses saw it, he was astonished at the sight; but as he went
        near to look more closely, the voice of the Lord came [to him, saying]: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u2018I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham and of Isaac
        and of Jacob.\u2019 Moses trembled with fear and did not dare to look. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u2018Remove the sandals from your feet,
        for the place where you are standing is holy ground [worthy of reverence
        and respect]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "I have most certainly seen the oppression of My people in Egypt and
        have heard their groaning, and I have come down to rescue them. Now come,
        and I will send you to Egypt [as My messenger].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThis Moses whom they rejected, saying, \u2018Who made you a
        ruler and a judge?\u2019 is the very one whom God sent to be both a ruler
        and a deliverer, with the [protecting and helping] hand of the Angel who
        appeared to him in the thorn bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'This man led them out [of Egypt] after performing wonders and signs
        in the land of Egypt and at the Red Sea and in the wilderness for forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "This is the Moses who said to the children of Israel, \u2018God will
        raise up for you a Prophet  like me from your countrymen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'This is the one who was in the congregation in the wilderness together
        with the Angel who spoke to him on Mount Sinai, and who was with our fathers;
        and he received living oracles [divine words that still live] to be handed
        down to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Our fathers were unwilling to be subject to him [and refused to listen
        to him]. They rejected him, and in their hearts turned back to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "They said to Aaron, \u2018Make for us gods who will go before us;
        for this Moses who led us out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has
        happened to him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'In those days they made a calf and brought a sacrifice to the idol,
        and rejoiced and celebrated over the works of their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But God turned away [from them] and handed them over to serve the
        host of heaven. As it is written and forever remains written in the book
        of the prophets, \u2018It was not [really] to Me that you offered victims
        and sacrifices for forty years in the wilderness, was it, O house of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "You also took along the tabernacle (portable temple) of Moloch and
        the star of the god Rompha, the images which you made to worship; and I will
        remove you beyond Babylon [carrying you away into exile].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201COur fathers had the tabernacle of testimony in the wilderness,
        just as God directed Moses to make it according to the pattern which he had
        seen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Our fathers also brought it in [with them into the land] with Joshua
        when they dispossessed the nations whom God drove out before our fathers,
        [and so it remained here] until the time of David, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'who found favor (grace, spiritual blessing) in the sight of God and
        asked that he might [be allowed to] find a dwelling place for the God of
        Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But it was Solomon who built a house for Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'However, the Most High [the One infinitely exalted above humanity]
        does not dwell in houses made by human hands; as the prophet [Isaiah] says,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u2018Heaven is My throne,And the earth is the footstool for My feet;What
        kind of house will you build for Me?\u2019 says the Lord,\u2018Or what place
        is there for My rest?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Was it not My hand that made all these things?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CYou stiff-necked and stubborn people, uncircumcised in heart
        and ears, you are always actively resisting the Holy Spirit. You are doing
        just as your fathers did. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Which one of the prophets did your fathers not persecute? They killed
        those who proclaimed beforehand the coming of the Righteous One, whose betrayers
        and murderers you have now become; '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: Stephen Put to Death'
      title: Stephen Put to Death
      number: 53
      content: "you who received the law as ordained and delivered to you by angels,
        and yet you did not obey it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Now when they heard this [accusation and understood its implication],
        they were cut to the heart, and they began grinding their teeth [in rage]
        at him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'But he, being full of the Holy Spirit and led by Him, gazed into
        heaven and saw the glory [the great splendor and majesty] of God, and Jesus
        standing at the right hand of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "and he said, \u201CLook! I see the heavens opened up [in welcome]
        and the Son of Man standing at the right hand of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'But they shouted with loud voices, and covered their ears and together
        rushed at him [considering him guilty of blasphemy]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Then they drove him out of the city and began stoning him; and the
        witnesses placed their outer robes at the feet of a young man named Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "They continued stoning Stephen as he called on the Lord and said,
        \u201CLord Jesus, receive and accept and welcome my spirit!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Then falling on his knees [in worship], he cried out loudly, \u201CLord,
        do not hold this sin against them [do not charge them]!\u201D When he had
        said this, he fell asleep [in death]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Persecutes the Church'
      title: Saul Persecutes the Church
      number: 1
      content: "  Saul wholeheartedly approved of Stephen\u2019s death.  And on that
        day a great and relentless persecution broke out against the church in Jerusalem;
        and the believers were all scattered throughout the regions of Judea and
        Samaria, except for the apostles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Some devout men buried Stephen, and mourned greatly over him [expressing
        a personal sense of loss]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Philip in Samaria'
      title: Philip in Samaria
      number: 3
      content: 'But Saul began ravaging the church [and assaulting believers]; entering
        house after house and dragging off men and women, putting them in prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now those [believers] who had been scattered went from place to place
        preaching the word [the good news of salvation through Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Philip [the evangelist] went down to the city of Samaria and began
        proclaiming Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed) to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The crowds gathered and were paying close attention to everything
        Philip said, as they heard [the message] and saw the [miraculous] signs which
        he was doing [validating his message]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For unclean spirits (demons), shouting loudly, were coming out of
        many who were possessed; and many who had been paralyzed and lame were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So there was great rejoicing in that city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now there was a man named Simon, who previously practiced magic in
        the city and amazed the people of Samaria, claiming to be someone great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They all paid [a great deal of] attention to him, from the least
        to the greatest, saying, \u201CThis man is what is called the Great Power
        of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They were paying attention to him because for a long time he had
        mystified and dazzled them with his magic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when they believed Philip as he preached the good news about
        the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were being baptized,
        both men and women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Even Simon believed [Philip\u2019s message of salvation]; and after
        being baptized, he continued on with Philip, and as he watched the attesting
        signs and great miracles taking place, he was constantly amazed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When the apostles in Jerusalem heard that [the people of] Samaria
        had accepted the word of God, they sent Peter and John to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They came down and prayed for them that they might receive the Holy
        Spirit; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'for He had not yet fallen on any of them; they had simply been baptized
        in the name of the Lord Jesus [as His possession]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Peter and John laid their hands on them [one by one], and they
        received the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now when Simon saw that the Spirit was given through the laying on
        of the apostles\u2019 hands, he offered them money, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "saying, \u201CGive me this authority and power too, so that anyone
        on whom I lay my hands may receive the Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Peter said to him, \u201CMay your money be destroyed along with
        you, because you thought you could buy the [free] gift of God with money! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have no part or share in this matter, because your heart (motive,
        purpose) is not right before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So repent of this wickedness of yours, and pray to the Lord that,
        if possible, this thought of your heart may be forgiven you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For I see that you are provoked by bitterness and bound by sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: An Ethiopian Receives Christ'
      title: An Ethiopian Receives Christ
      number: 24
      content: "But Simon answered, \u201CPray to the Lord for me both of you, so
        that nothing of what you have said will come upon me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So, when Peter and John had given their testimony and preached the
        word of the Lord, they started back to Jerusalem, preaching the good news
        [about salvation] in many Samaritan villages [along the way].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But an angel of the Lord said to Philip, \u201CGet up and go south
        to the road that runs from Jerusalem down to Gaza.\u201D (This is a desert
        road). "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So he got up and went; and there was an Ethiopian eunuch [a man of
        great authority], a court official of Candace, queen of the Ethiopians, who
        was in charge of all her treasure. He had come to Jerusalem to worship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and he was returning, and sitting in his chariot he was reading [the
        scroll of] the prophet Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the [Holy] Spirit said to Philip, \u201CGo up and join this
        chariot.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Philip ran up and heard the man reading the prophet Isaiah, and asked,
        \u201CDo you understand what you are reading?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CWell, how could I [understand] unless someone
        guides me [correctly]?\u201D And he invited Philip to come up and sit with
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now this was the passage of Scripture which he was reading:\u201CLike
        a sheep He was led to the slaughter;And as a lamb before its shearer is silent,So
        He does not open His mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "In humiliation His judgment was taken away [justice was denied Him].Who
        will describe His generation?For His life is taken from the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The eunuch replied to Philip, \u201CPlease tell me, about whom does
        the prophet say this? About himself or about someone else?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then Philip spoke and beginning with this Scripture he preached Jesus
        to him [explaining that He is the promised Messiah and the source of salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "As they continued along the road, they came to some water; and the
        eunuch exclaimed, \u201CLook! Water! What forbids me from being baptized?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "[Philip said to him, \u201CIf you believe with all your heart, you
        may.\u201D And he replied, \u201CI do believe that Jesus Christ is the Son
        of God.\u201D]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And he ordered that the chariot be stopped; and both Philip and the
        eunuch went down into the water, and Philip baptized him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'When they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord [suddenly]
        took Philip [and carried him] away [to a different place]; and the eunuch
        no longer saw him, but he went on his way rejoicing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: But Philip found himself at Azotus, and as he passed through he preached
        the good news [of salvation] to all the cities, until he came to Caesarea
        [Maritima].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Conversion of Saul'
      title: The Conversion of Saul
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Saul, still breathing threats and murder against the disciples
        of the Lord [and relentless in his search for believers], went to the high
        priest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and he asked for letters [of authority] from him to the synagogues
        at Damascus, so that if he found any men or women there belonging to the
        Way [believers, followers of Jesus the Messiah], men and women alike, he
        could arrest them and bring them bound [with chains] to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As he traveled he approached Damascus, and suddenly a light from
        heaven flashed around him [displaying the glory and majesty of Christ]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and he fell to the ground and heard a voice [from heaven] saying
        to him, <JESUS>\u201CSaul, Saul, why are you persecuting </JESUS>and oppressing
        Me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CWho are You, Lord?\u201D And He answered,  <JESUS>\u201CI
        am Jesus whom you are persecuting,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>now get up and go into the city, and you will be told what
        you must do.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The men who were traveling with him [were terrified and] stood speechless,
        hearing the voice but seeing no one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Saul got up from the ground, but though his eyes were open, he could
        see nothing; so they led him by the hand and brought him into Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he was unable to see for three days, and he neither ate nor drank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now in Damascus there was a disciple named Ananias; and the Lord
        said to him in a vision, <JESUS>\u201CAnanias.\u201D</JESUS> And he answered,
        \u201CHere I am, Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGet up and go to the street
        called </JESUS><JESUS>Straight, and ask at the house of Judas for a man from
        Tarsus named Saul; for he is praying</JESUS> [there], "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>and in a vision he has seen a man named Ananias come in and
        place his hands on him, so that he may regain his sight.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Ananias answered, \u201CLord, I have heard from many people about
        this man, especially how much suffering and evil he has brought on Your saints
        (God\u2019s people) at Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and here [in Damascus] he has authority from the high priests to
        put in chains all who call on Your name [confessing You as Savior].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo, for this man is a</JESUS>
        [deliberately] <JESUS>chosen instrument of Mine, to bear My name before the
        Gentiles and kings and the sons of Israel;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>for I will make clear to him how much he must suffer </JESUS>and
        endure for My name\u2019s sake.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Ananias left and entered the house, and he laid his hands on Saul
        and said, \u201CBrother Saul, the Lord Jesus, who appeared to you on the
        road as you came [to Damascus], has sent me so that you may regain your sight
        and be filled with the Holy Spirit [in order to proclaim Christ to both Jews
        and Gentiles].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Immediately something like scales fell from Saul\u2019s eyes, and
        he regained his sight. Then he got up and was baptized; "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Saul Begins to Preach Christ'
      title: Saul Begins to Preach Christ
      number: 19
      content: 'and he took some food and was strengthened.  For several days [afterward]
        Saul remained with the disciples who were at Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And immediately he began proclaiming Jesus in the synagogues, saying,
        \u201CThis Man is the Son of God [the promised Messiah]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "All those who heard him continued to be amazed and said, \u201CIs
        this not the man who in Jerusalem attacked those who called on this name
        [of Jesus], and had come here [to Damascus] for the express purpose of bringing
        them bound [with chains] before the chief priests?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But Saul increased in strength more and more, and continued to perplex
        the Jews who lived in Damascus by examining [theological evidence] and proving
        [with Scripture] that this Jesus is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After considerable time had passed [about three years or so], the
        Jews plotted together to kill him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "but their plot became known to Saul. They were also watching the
        city\u2019s gates day and night so they could kill him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'but his disciples took him at night and let him down through an opening
        in the wall, lowering him in a large basket.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When he arrived in Jerusalem, he tried to join the disciples; but
        they were all afraid of him, not believing that he really was a disciple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'However, Barnabas took him and brought him to the apostles, and described
        to them how Saul had seen the Lord on the road [to Damascus], and how He
        had spoken to him, and how at Damascus Saul had preached openly and spoken
        confidently in the name of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So he was with them, moving around freely [as one among them] in
        Jerusalem, speaking out boldly in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He was talking and arguing with the Hellenists (Greek-speaking Jews);
        but they were attempting to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When the brothers found out [about the plot], they brought him down
        to Caesarea [Maritima] and sent him off to Tarsus [his home town].  '
      comments: []
    - name: "31: Peter\u2019s Ministry"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Ministry"
      number: 31
      content: 'So the church throughout Judea and Galilee and Samaria enjoyed peace
        [without persecution], being built up [in wisdom, virtue, and faith]; and
        walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort and encouragement of the
        Holy Spirit, it continued to grow [in numbers].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now as Peter was traveling throughout the land, he went down to [visit]
        the saints (God\u2019s people) who lived at Lydda. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'There he found a man named Aeneas, who had been bedridden for eight
        years and was paralyzed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Peter said to him, \u201CAeneas, Jesus Christ heals you. Get up and
        make your bed.\u201D Immediately Aeneas got up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then all who lived at Lydda and the plain of Sharon saw [what had
        happened to] him, and they turned to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now in Joppa there was a disciple named Tabitha, (which translated
        into Greek means Dorcas). She was rich in acts of kindness and charity which
        she continually did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'During that time it happened that she became sick and died; and when
        they had washed her body, they laid it in an upstairs room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Since Lydda was near Joppa, the disciples, hearing that Peter was
        there, sent two men to him, urging him, \u201CCome to us without delay.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So Peter got up [at once] and went with them. When he arrived, they
        brought him into the upstairs room; and all the widows stood beside him,
        weeping and showing [him] all the tunics and robes that Dorcas used to make
        while she was with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But Peter sent them all out [of the room] and knelt down and prayed;
        then turning to the body he said, \u201CTabitha, arise!\u201D And she opened
        her eyes, and when she saw Peter, she sat up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And he gave her his hand and helped her up; and then he called in
        the saints (God\u2019s people) and the widows, and he presented her [to them]
        alive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'This became known all over Joppa, and many came to believe in the
        Lord [that is, to adhere to and trust in and rely on Jesus as Christ and
        Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And so it was that Peter stayed in Joppa for many days with Simon,
        a tanner.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Cornelius\u2019 Vision"
      title: "Cornelius\u2019 Vision"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now at Caesarea [Maritima] there was a man named Cornelius, a centurion
        of what was known as the Italian Regiment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a devout man and one who, along with all his household, feared God.
        He made many charitable donations to the Jewish people, and prayed to God
        always. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "About the ninth hour (3:00 p.m.) of the day he clearly saw in a vision
        an angel of God who had come to him and said, \u201CCornelius!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Cornelius was frightened and stared intently at him and said, \u201CWhat
        is it, lord (sir)?\u201D And the angel said to him, \u201CYour prayers and
        gifts of charity have ascended as a memorial offering before God [an offering
        made in remembrance of His past blessings]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now send men to Joppa and have them call for a man named Simon, who
        is also called Peter [and invite him here]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "he is staying with Simon the tanner, whose house is by the sea.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the angel who was speaking to him had gone, Cornelius called
        two of his servants and a devout soldier from among his own personal attendants; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and after explaining everything to them, he sent them to Joppa.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The next day, as they were on their way and were approaching the
        city, Peter went up on the roof of the house about the sixth hour (noon)
        to pray, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but he became hungry and wanted something to eat. While the meal
        was being prepared he fell into a trance; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and he saw the sky opened up, and an object like a great sheet descending,
        lowered by its four corners to the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and it contained all kinds of four-footed animals and crawling creatures
        of the earth and birds of the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "A voice came to him, \u201CGet up, Peter, kill and eat!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CNot at all, Lord, for I have never eaten anything
        that is common (unholy) and [ceremonially] unclean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the voice came to him a second time, \u201CWhat God has cleansed
        and pronounced clean, no longer consider common (unholy).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This happened three times, and then immediately the object was taken
        up into heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now Peter was still perplexed and completely at a loss as to what
        his vision could mean when the men who had been sent by Cornelius, having
        asked directions to Simon\u2019s house, arrived at the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they called out to ask whether Simon, who was also called Peter,
        was staying there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "While Peter was thoughtfully considering the vision, the Spirit said
        to him, \u201CNow listen, three men are looking for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Get up, go downstairs and go with them without hesitating or doubting,
        because I have sent them Myself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Peter went down to the men and said, \u201CI am the one you are looking
        for. For what reason have you come?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "They said, \u201CCornelius, a centurion, an upright and God-fearing
        man well spoken of by all the Jewish people, was divinely instructed by a
        holy angel to send for you to come to his house and hear what you have to
        say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Peter at Caesarea'
      title: Peter at Caesarea
      number: 23
      content: 'So Peter invited them in and gave them lodging [for the night]. 
        The next day Peter got up and left with them, and some of the brothers from
        Joppa went with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'On the following day he [and the others] entered Caesarea. Cornelius
        was waiting for them, and had called together his relatives and close friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Peter arrived, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet
        and worshiped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Peter raised him up, saying, \u201CStand up; I too am only a
        man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As Peter talked with him, he entered [the house] and found a large
        group of people assembled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He said to them, \u201CYou know that it is unlawful for a Jewish
        man to associate with or befriend a Gentile, or to visit him; and yet God
        has shown me that I am not to call anyone common or [ceremonially] unclean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore when I was sent for, I came without raising an objection.
        So I ask for what reason have you sent for me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Cornelius said, \u201CFour days ago to this hour, I was praying in
        my house during the ninth hour (3:00-4:00 p.m.); and a man [dressed] in bright,
        dazzling clothing suddenly stood before me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and he said, \u2018Cornelius, your prayer has been heard, and your
        acts of charity have been remembered before God [so that He is about to help
        you]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore send word to Joppa and invite Simon, who is also called
        Peter, to come to you. He is staying at the house of Simon the tanner by
        the sea.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Gentiles Hear Good News'
      title: Gentiles Hear Good News
      number: 33
      content: "So I sent for you at once, and you have been kind enough to come.
        Now then, we are all here present before God to listen to everything that
        you have been instructed by the Lord [to say].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Opening his mouth, Peter said:\u201CMost certainly I understand now
        that God is not one to show partiality [to people as though Gentiles were
        excluded from God\u2019s blessing], "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'but in every nation the person who fears God and does what is right
        [by seeking Him] is acceptable and welcomed by Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "You know the message which He sent to the sons of Israel, announcing
        the good news of peace through Jesus Christ, who is Lord of all\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "you know the things that have taken place throughout Judea, starting
        in Galilee after the baptism preached by John\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'how God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with
        great power; and He went around doing good and healing all who were oppressed
        by the devil, because God was with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'We are [personally] eyewitnesses of everything that He did both in
        the land of the Jews and in Jerusalem [in particular]. They also put Him
        to death by hanging Him on a cross; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'God raised Him [to life] on the third day and caused Him to be plainly
        seen, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'not to all the people, but to witnesses who were chosen and designated
        beforehand by God, that is, to us who ate and drank together with Him after
        He rose from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'He commanded us to preach to the people [both Jew and Gentile], and
        to solemnly testify that He is the One who has been appointed and ordained
        by God as Judge of the living and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "All the prophets testify about Him, that through His name everyone
        who believes in Him [whoever trusts in and relies on Him, accepting Him as
        Savior and Messiah] receives forgiveness of sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "While Peter was still speaking these words, the Holy Spirit fell
        on all those who were listening to the message [confirming God\u2019s acceptance
        of Gentiles]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'All the circumcised believers who came with Peter were amazed, because
        the gift of the Holy Spirit had been poured out even on the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For they heard them talking in [unknown] tongues (languages) and
        exalting and magnifying and praising God. Then Peter said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CCan anyone refuse water for these people to be baptized, since
        they have received the Holy Spirit just as we did?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: And he ordered that they be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ.
        Then they asked him to stay there for a few days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter Reports at Jerusalem'
      title: Peter Reports at Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the apostles and the believers who were throughout Judea heard
        [with astonishment] that the Gentiles also had received and accepted the
        word of God [the message concerning salvation through Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So when Peter went up to Jerusalem, those of the circumcision [certain
        Jewish believers who followed the Law] took issue with him [for violating
        Jewish customs], '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "saying, \u201CYou went to uncircumcised men and [even] ate with them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Peter began [at the beginning] and explained [the events] to
        them step by step, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI was in the city of Joppa praying; and in a trance I saw a
        vision of an object coming down from heaven, like a huge sheet being lowered
        by the four corners; and [it descended until] it came right down to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and looking closely at it, I saw all kinds of the four-footed animals
        of the earth and the wild beasts and the crawling creatures and the birds
        of the air [both clean and unclean according to the Law], '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and I also heard a voice saying to me, \u2018Get up, Peter; kill
        and eat.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But I said, \u2018Not at all, Lord; for nothing common (unholy) or
        [ceremonially] unclean has ever entered my mouth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the voice from heaven answered a second time, \u2018What God
        has cleansed and pronounced clean, no longer consider common (unholy).\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This happened three times, and everything was drawn up again into
        heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And right then the three men who had been sent to me from Caesarea
        arrived at the house where we were staying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The Spirit told me to go with them without the slightest hesitation.
        So these six brothers also went with me and we went to the man\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Cornelius told us how he had seen the angel standing in his house,
        saying, \u2018Send word to Joppa and have Simon, who is also called Peter,
        brought here; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "he will bring a message to you by which you will be saved [and granted
        eternal life], you and all your household.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell on them just as He did
        on us at the beginning [at Pentecost]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I remembered the word of the Lord, how He used to say, <JESUS>\u2018John
        baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So, if God gave Gentiles the same gift [equally] as He gave us after
        we accepted and believed and trusted in the Lord Jesus Christ [as Savior],
        who was I to interfere or stand in God\u2019s way?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Church at Antioch'
      title: The Church at Antioch
      number: 18
      content: "When they heard this, they quieted down and glorified and praised
        God, saying, \u201CThen God has also granted to the Gentiles repentance that
        leads to eternal life [that is, real life after earthly death].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So then [since they were unaware of these developments] those who
        were scattered because of the persecution that occurred in connection with
        [the stoning of] Stephen traveled as far as Phoenicia and Cyprus and Antioch,
        without telling the message [of salvation through Christ] to anyone except
        Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But there were some of them, men of Cyprus and Cyrene, who came to
        Antioch and began speaking to the Greeks as well, proclaiming [to them] the
        good news about the Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the hand (the power and presence) of the Lord was with them,
        and a great number who believed turned to the Lord [for salvation, accepting
        and drawing near to Jesus as Messiah and Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The news of this reached the ears of the church in Jerusalem, and
        they sent Barnabas to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he arrived and saw the grace of God [that was bestowed on them],
        he rejoiced and began to encourage them all with an unwavering heart to stay
        true and devoted to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For Barnabas was a good man [privately and publicly\u2014his godly
        character benefited both himself and others] and he was full of the Holy
        Spirit and full of faith [in Jesus the Messiah, through whom believers have
        everlasting life]. And a great number of people were brought to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Barnabas left for Tarsus to search for Saul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and when he found him, he brought him back to Antioch. For an entire
        year they met [with others] in the church and instructed large numbers; and
        it was in Antioch that the disciples were first called Christians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now at this time some prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'One of them named Agabus stood up and prophesied through the [Holy]
        Spirit that a severe famine would come on the entire world. And this did
        happen during the reign of Claudius. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So the disciples decided to send a contribution, each according to
        his individual ability, to the believers who lived in Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And this they did, sending the contribution to the elders by Barnabas
        and Saul.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Peter\u2019s Arrest and Escape"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Arrest and Escape"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now at that time Herod [Agrippa I] the king [of the Jews] arrested
        some who belonged to the church, intending to harm them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he had James the brother of John put to death with a sword; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and when he saw that it pleased the Jews, he proceeded to have Peter
        arrested as well. This was during the days of Unleavened Bread [the Passover
        week]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When he had seized Peter, he put him in prison, turning him over
        to four squads of soldiers of four each to guard him [in rotation throughout
        the night], planning after the Passover to bring him out before the people
        [for execution]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Peter was kept in prison, but fervent and persistent prayer for
        him was being made to God by the church.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The very night before Herod was to bring him forward, Peter was sleeping
        between two soldiers, bound with two chains, and sentries were in front of
        the door guarding the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Suddenly, an angel of the Lord appeared [beside him] and a light
        shone in the cell. The angel struck Peter\u2019s side and awakened him, saying,
        \u201CGet up quickly!\u201D And the chains fell off his hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The angel said to him, \u201CPrepare yourself and strap on your sandals
        [to get ready for whatever may happen].\u201D And he did so. Then the angel
        told him, \u201CPut on your robe and follow me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Peter went out following the angel. He did not realize that what
        was being done by the angel was real, but thought he was seeing a vision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they had passed the first guard and the second, they came to
        the iron gate that leads into the city. Of its own accord it swung open for
        them; and they went out and went along one street, and at once the angel
        left him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When Peter came to his senses, he said, \u201CNow I know for certain
        that the Lord has sent His angel and has rescued me from the hand of Herod
        and from all that the Jewish people were expecting [to do to me].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When he realized what had happened, he went to the house of Mary
        the mother of John, who was also called Mark, where many [believers] were
        gathered together and were praying continually [and had been praying all
        night]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he knocked at the door of the gateway, a servant-girl named
        Rhoda came to answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Recognizing Peter\u2019s voice, in her joy she failed to open the
        gate, but ran in and announced that Peter was standing in front of the gateway. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "They said to her, \u201CYou are out of your mind!\u201D But she kept
        insisting that it was so. They kept saying, \u201CIt is his angel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But [meanwhile] Peter continued knocking; and when they opened the
        door and saw him, they were completely amazed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But motioning to them with his hand to be quiet and listen, he described
        how the Lord had led him out of the prison. And he said, \u201CReport these
        things to James and the brothers and sisters.\u201D Then he left and went
        to another place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now when day came, there was no small disturbance among the soldiers
        over what had become of Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Death of Herod'
      title: Death of Herod
      number: 19
      content: 'When Herod had searched for him and could not find him, he interrogated
        the guards and commanded that they be led away to execution. Then he went
        down from Judea to Caesarea [Maritima] and spent some time there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Herod [Agrippa I] was extremely angry with the people of Tyre
        and Sidon; and their delegates came to him in a united group, and after persuading
        Blastus, the king\u2019s chamberlain [to support their cause], they asked
        for peace, because their country was fed by [imports of grain and other goods
        from] the king\u2019s country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'On an appointed day Herod dressed himself in his royal robes, sat
        on his throne (tribunal, rostrum) and began delivering a speech to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The assembled people kept shouting, \u201CIt is the voice of a god
        and not of a man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And at once an angel of the Lord struck him down because he did not
        give God the glory [and instead permitted himself to be worshiped], and he
        was eaten by worms and died [five days later].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But the word of the Lord [the good news about salvation through Christ]
        continued to grow and spread [increasing in effectiveness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Barnabas and Saul came back from Jerusalem when they had completed
        their mission, bringing with them John, who was also called Mark.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: First Missionary Journey'
      title: First Missionary Journey
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the church at Antioch there were prophets [who spoke a new
        message of God to the people] and teachers: Barnabas, Simeon who was called
        Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen who had been brought up with Herod [Antipas]
        the tetrarch, and Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "While they were serving the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit said,
        \u201CSet apart for Me Barnabas and Saul (Paul) for the work to which I have
        called them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then after fasting and praying, they laid their hands on them [in
        approval and dedication] and sent them away [on their first journey].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So then, being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went down to Seleucia,
        and from there they sailed to Cyprus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Barnabas and Saul arrived at Salamis, they began to preach the
        word of God [proclaiming the message of eternal salvation through faith in
        Christ] in the synagogues of the Jews; and they also had John [Mark] as their
        assistant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When they had traveled through the entire island [of Cyprus] as far
        as Paphos, they found a sorcerer, a Jewish false prophet named Bar-Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'who was [closely associated] with the proconsul [of the province],
        Sergius Paulus, an intelligent and sensible man. He called for Barnabas and
        Saul and wanted to hear the word of God [concerning eternal salvation through
        faith in Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Elymas the sorcerer (for that is how his name is translated)
        opposed them, trying to turn the proconsul away from accepting the faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Saul, who was also known as Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit
        and led by Him, looked steadily at Elymas, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said, \u201CYou [Elymas] who are full of every [kind of] deceit,
        and every [kind of] fraud, you son of the devil, enemy of everything that
        is right and good, will you never stop perverting the straight paths of the
        Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now, watch! The hand of the Lord is on you, and you will be blind,
        [so blind that you will be] unable to see the sun for a time.\u201D Immediately
        a mist and darkness fell upon him, and he groped around, seeking people to
        lead him by the hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The proconsul believed [the message of salvation] when he saw what
        had happened, being astonished at the teaching concerning the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now Paul and his companions sailed from Paphos and came to Perga
        in Pamphylia; but John [Mark] left them and went back to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now they went on from Perga and arrived at Antioch in Pisidia, and
        on the Sabbath day they went into the synagogue and sat down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "After the reading of the Law and the [writings of the] Prophets,
        the officials of the synagogue sent word to them, saying, \u201CBrothers
        (kinsmen), if you have any word of encouragement for the people, say it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Paul stood up, and motioning with his hand, he said,\u201CMen
        of Israel, and you who fear God, listen! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The God of this people Israel chose our fathers and made the people
        great and numerous during their stay [as foreigners] in the land of Egypt,
        and then with an uplifted arm He led them out of there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For a period of about forty years He put up with their behavior in
        the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When He had destroyed seven nations in the land of Canaan, He gave
        their land [to our ancestors] as an inheritance\u2014this took about four
        hundred and fifty years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After this, He gave them judges until the prophet Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they asked for a king, and God gave them Saul the son of Kish,
        a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when He had removed him, He raised up David to be their king:
        of him He testified and said, \u2018I have found David the son of Jesse,
        a man after My own heart [conforming to My will and purposes], who will do
        all My will.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "From this man\u2019s descendants God has brought to Israel a Savior,
        [in the person of] Jesus, according to His promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Before His coming John [the Baptist] had preached a baptism of repentance
        to all the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And as John was finishing his course [of ministry], he kept saying,
        \u2018What or who do you think that I am? I am not He [the Christ]; but be
        aware, One is coming after me whose sandals I am not worthy to untie [even
        as His slave]!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBrothers, sons of Abraham\u2019s family, and those among you
        who fear God, to us has been sent the message of this salvation [obtained
        through faith in Jesus Christ]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For those who live in Jerusalem, and their rulers, who failed to
        recognize or understand both Jesus and the voices of the prophets which are
        read every Sabbath, have fulfilled these [very prophecies] by condemning
        Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And though they found no cause or charge deserving death, they asked
        Pilate to have Him executed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when they had finished carrying out everything that was written
        [in Scripture] about Him, they took Him down from the cross and laid Him
        in a tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But God raised Him from the dead; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and for many days (forty) He appeared to those who came up with Him
        from Galilee to Jerusalem, the very ones who are now His witnesses to the
        people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And we are bringing you the good news of the promise made to our
        fathers (ancestors), '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "that God has completely fulfilled this promise to our children by
        raising up Jesus, as it is also written in the second Psalm, \u2018You are
        My Son; today I have begotten (fathered) You.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And [as for the fact] that He raised Him from the dead, never again
        to return to decay [in the grave], He has spoken in this way: \u2018I will
        give you the holy and sure  blessings  of David [those blessings and mercies
        that were promised to him].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "For this reason He also says in another Psalm, \u2018You will not
        allow Your Holy One to see decay.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For David, after he had served the purpose of God in his own generation,
        fell asleep and was buried among his fathers and experienced decay [in the
        grave]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'but He whom God raised [to life] did not experience decay [in the
        grave]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So let it be clearly known by you, brothers, that through Him forgiveness
        of sins is being proclaimed to you; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and through Him everyone who believes [who acknowledges Jesus as
        Lord and Savior and follows Him] is justified and declared free of guilt
        from all things, from which you could not be justified and freed of guilt
        through the Law of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Therefore be careful, so that the thing spoken of in the [writings
        of the] Prophets does not come upon you:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u2018Look, you mockers, and marvel, and perish  and  vanish away;For
        I am doing a work in your days,A work which you will never believe, even
        if someone describes it to you [telling you about it in detail].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'As Paul and Barnabas were leaving [the synagogue], the people kept
        begging that these things might be spoken to them on the next Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Paul Turns to the Gentiles'
      title: Paul Turns to the Gentiles
      number: 43
      content: 'When the congregation of the synagogue had been dismissed, many of
        the Jews and the devout converts to Judaism followed Paul and Barnabas, who,
        talking to them were urging them to continue in the grace of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On the next Sabbath almost the entire city gathered together to hear
        the word of the Lord [about salvation through faith in Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'But when the Jews saw the crowds, they were filled with jealousy
        and began contradicting the things said by Paul, and were slandering him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And [at the same time] Paul and Barnabas spoke out boldly and confidently,
        saying, \u201CIt was necessary that God\u2019s message [of salvation through
        faith in Christ] be spoken to you [Jews] first. Since you repudiate it and
        judge yourselves unworthy of eternal life, now we turn to the Gentiles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "For that is what the Lord has commanded us, saying,\u2018I have placed
        You as a light for the Gentiles,So that You may bring [the message of eternal]
        salvation to the end of the earth.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When the Gentiles heard this, they began rejoicing and glorifying
        [praising and giving thanks for] the word of the Lord; and all those who
        had been appointed (designated, ordained) to eternal life [by God] believed
        [in Jesus as the Christ and their Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And so the word of the Lord [regarding salvation] was being spread
        through the entire region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'But the Jews incited the devout, prominent women and the leading
        men of the city, and instigated persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and
        drove them forcibly out of their district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'But they shook its dust from their feet in protest against them and
        went to Iconium. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: And the disciples were continually filled [throughout their hearts
        and souls] with joy and with the Holy Spirit.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Acceptance and Opposition'
      title: Acceptance and Opposition
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in Iconium Paul and Barnabas went into the Jewish synagogue
        together and spoke in such a way [with such power and boldness] that a large
        number of Jews as well as Greeks believed [and confidently accepted Jesus
        as Savior]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but the unbelieving Jews [who rejected Jesus as Messiah] stirred
        up and embittered the minds of the Gentiles against the believers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Paul and Barnabas stayed for a long time, speaking boldly and
        confidently for the Lord, who continued to testify to the word of His grace,
        granting that signs and wonders (attesting miracles) be done by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the people of the city were divided; some were siding with the
        Jews, and some with the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When there was an attempt by both the Gentiles and the Jews, together
        with their rulers, to shamefully mistreat and to stone them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'they, aware of the situation, escaped to Lystra and Derbe, [taking
        refuge in the] cities of Lycaonia, and the neighboring region; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and there they continued to preach the good news.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now at Lystra a man sat who was unable to use his feet, for he was
        crippled from birth and had never walked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This man was listening to Paul as he spoke, and Paul looked intently
        at him and saw that he had faith to be healed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said with a loud voice, \u201CStand up on your feet.\u201D And
        he jumped up and began to walk. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the crowds, when they saw what Paul had done, raised their voices,
        shouting in the Lycaonian language, \u201CThe gods have come down to us in
        human form!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They began calling Barnabas, Zeus [chief of the Greek gods], and
        Paul, Hermes [messenger of the Greek gods], since he took the lead in speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The priest of Zeus, whose temple was at the entrance of the city,
        brought bulls and garlands to the city gates, and wanted to offer sacrifices
        with the crowds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But when the apostles Barnabas and Paul heard about it, they tore
        their robes and rushed out into the crowd, shouting, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMen, why are you doing these things? We too are only men of
        the same nature as you, bringing the good news to you, so that you turn from
        these useless and meaningless things to the living God, who made the heaven
        and the earth and the sea and everything that is in them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In generations past He permitted all the nations to go their own
        ways; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "yet He did not leave Himself without some witness [as evidence of
        Himself], in that He kept constantly doing good things and showing you kindness,
        and giving you rains from heaven and productive seasons, filling your hearts
        with food and happiness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Even saying these words, with difficulty they prevented the people
        from offering sacrifices to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But Jews arrived from Antioch and Iconium, and having won over the
        crowds, they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, thinking he was
        dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But the disciples formed a circle around him, and he got up and went
        back into the city; and the next day he went on with Barnabas to Derbe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They preached the good news to that city and made many disciples,
        then they returned to Lystra and to Iconium and to Antioch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "strengthening and establishing the hearts of the disciples; encouraging
        them to remain firm in the faith, saying, \u201CIt is through many tribulations
        and hardships that we must enter the kingdom of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When they had appointed elders for them in every church, having prayed
        with fasting, they entrusted them to the Lord in whom they believed [and
        joyfully accepted as the Messiah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then they passed through Pisidia and came to Pamphylia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When they had spoken the word [of salvation through faith in Christ]
        in Perga, they went down to Attalia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'From there they sailed back to Antioch, where they had been entrusted
        to the grace of God for the work which they had now completed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Arriving there, they gathered the church together and began to report
        [in great detail] everything that God had done with them and how He had opened
        to the Gentiles a door of faith [in Jesus as the Messiah and Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And they stayed there a long time with the disciples.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Council at Jerusalem'
      title: The Council at Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "  Some men came down from Judea and began teaching the brothers,
        \u201CUnless you are circumcised in accordance with the custom of Moses,
        you cannot be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Paul and Barnabas disagreed greatly and debated with them, so it
        was determined that Paul and Barnabas and some of the others from their group
        would go up to Jerusalem to the apostles and the elders [and confer with
        them] concerning this issue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So, after being supplied and sent on their way by the church, they
        went through both Phoenicia and Samaria telling in detail the conversion
        of the Gentiles, and they brought great joy to all the believers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When they arrived in Jerusalem, they were received warmly by the
        church and the apostles and the elders, and they reported to them all the
        things that God had accomplished through them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But some from the sect of the Pharisees who had believed [in Jesus
        as the Messiah] stood up and said, \u201CIt is necessary to circumcise the
        Gentile converts and to direct them to observe the Law of Moses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The apostles and the elders came together to consider this matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "After a long debate, Peter got up and said to them, \u201CBrothers,
        you know that in the early days God made a choice among you, that by my mouth
        the Gentiles would hear the message of the gospel and believe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God, who knows and understands the heart, testified to them,
        giving them the Holy Spirit, just as He also did to us; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and He made no distinction between us and them, cleansing their hearts
        by faith [in Jesus]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now then, why are you testing God by placing a yoke on the neck of
        the disciples which neither our fathers nor we have been able to endure? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But we believe that we are saved through the [precious, undeserved]
        grace of the Lord Jesus [which makes us free of the guilt of sin and grants
        us eternal life], in just the same way as they are.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: James\u2019 Judgment"
      title: "James\u2019 Judgment"
      number: 12
      content: 'All the people remained silent, and they listened [attentively] to
        Barnabas and Paul as they described all the signs and wonders (attesting
        miracles) that God had done through them among the Gentiles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When they had finished speaking, James replied, \u201CBrothers, listen
        to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Simeon (Simon Peter) has described how God first concerned Himself
        about taking from among the Gentiles a people for His name [to honor Him
        and be identified with Him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The words of the Prophets agree with this, just as it is written
        [in Scripture],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018After these things I will return,And I will rebuild the tent
        of David which has fallen;I will rebuild its ruins,And I will restore it,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So that the rest of mankind may seek the Lord,And all the Gentiles
        upon whom My name has been invoked,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Says the Lord,Who has been making these things known from long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore it is my judgment that we do not trouble and make it difficult
        for those who are turning to God among the Gentiles [by putting obstacles
        in their way], '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but that we write to them that they are to abstain from anything
        that has been contaminated by [being offered to] idols and from sexual impurity
        and from [eating the meat of] what has been strangled and from [the consumption
        of] blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For from ancient generations [the writing of] Moses has been preached
        in every city, since he is read aloud in the synagogues every Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the apostles and the elders, together with the whole church,
        decided to select some of their men to go to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas\u2014Judas,
        who was called Barsabbas, and Silas [also called Silvanus, both], leading
        men among the brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "With them they sent the following letter:\u201CThe apostles and the
        brothers who are the elders, to the brothers and sisters who are from the
        Gentiles in Antioch, Syria, and Cilicia, Greetings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Since we have heard that some of our men have troubled you with their
        teachings, causing distress and confusion\u2014men to whom we gave no such
        orders or instructions\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'it has been decided by us, having met together, to select men and
        send them to you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So we have sent Judas and Silas, who will report by word of mouth
        the same things [that we decided in our meeting].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For it seemed good to the Holy Spirit and to us not to place on you
        any greater burden than these essentials:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you abstain from things sacrificed to idols, and from [consuming]
        blood, and from [eating the meat of] things that have been strangled, and
        from sexual impurity. If you keep yourselves from these things, you will
        do well. Farewell.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when they were sent off, they went down to Antioch; and after
        assembling the congregation, they delivered the letter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And when they had read it, the people rejoiced greatly at the encouragement
        and comfort [it brought them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Judas and Silas, who were themselves prophets (divinely inspired
        spokesmen), encouraged and strengthened the believers with many words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'After spending some time there, they were sent back by the brothers
        with [the greeting of] peace to those who had sent them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '[However, Silas decided to stay there.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: "35: Paul\u2019s Second Missionary Journey"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Second Missionary Journey"
      number: 35
      content: 'But Paul and Barnabas remained in Antioch, and with many others also
        continued teaching and proclaiming the good news, the word of the Lord [concerning
        eternal salvation through faith in Christ].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "After some time Paul said to Barnabas, \u201CLet us go back and visit
        the brothers and sisters (believers) in every city where we preached the
        message of the Lord, and see how they are doing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Now Barnabas wanted to take [his cousin] John, who was called Mark,
        along with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But Paul kept insisting that they should not take along with them
        the one who had quit and deserted them in Pamphylia and had not gone on with
        them to the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And it became such a sharp disagreement that they separated from
        one another, and Barnabas took [John] Mark with him and sailed away to Cyprus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But Paul chose Silas [who was again in Antioch] and set out [on his
        second journey], commended by the brothers to the grace and favor of the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And he traveled through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Macedonian Vision'
      title: The Macedonian Vision
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Paul traveled to Derbe and also to Lystra. A disciple named
        Timothy was there, the son of a Jewish woman who was a believer [in Christ],
        however, his father was a Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Timothy was well spoken of by the brothers and sisters who were in
        Lystra and Iconium. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Paul wanted Timothy to go with him [as a missionary]; and he took
        him and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those places, since
        they all knew that his father was a Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As they traveled from town to town, they delivered the decrees decided
        on by the apostles and elders who were in Jerusalem, for the churches to
        observe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the churches were strengthened in the faith, and they continually
        increased in number day after day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now they passed through the territory of Phrygia and Galatia, after
        being forbidden by the Holy Spirit to speak the word in [the west coast province
        of] Asia [Minor]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and after they came to Mysia, they tried to go into Bithynia, but
        the Spirit of Jesus did not permit them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'so passing by Mysia, they went down to Troas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then a vision appeared to Paul in the night: a man from [the Roman
        province of] Macedonia was standing and pleading with him, saying, \u201CCome
        over to Macedonia and help us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when he had seen the vision, we (including Luke) tried to go
        on into Macedonia at once, concluding that God had called us to preach the
        gospel to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So setting sail from Troas, we ran a direct course to Samothrace,
        and the next day [went on] to Neapolis; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and from there [we came] to Philippi, which is a leading city of
        the district of Macedonia, a Roman colony. We stayed on in this city for
        several days; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: First Convert in Europe'
      title: First Convert in Europe
      number: 13
      content: 'and on the Sabbath day we went outside the city gate to the bank
        of the [Gangites] river, where we thought there would be a place of prayer,
        and we sat down and began speaking to the women who had come there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'A woman named Lydia, from the city of Thyatira, a dealer in purple
        fabrics who was [already] a worshiper of God, listened to us; and the Lord
        opened her heart to pay attention and to respond to the things said by Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when she was baptized, along with her household, she pleaded
        with us, saying, \u201CIf you have judged me and decided that I am faithful
        to the Lord [a true believer], come to my house and stay.\u201D And she persuaded
        us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It happened that as we were on our way to the place of prayer, we
        were met by a slave-girl who had a spirit of divination [that is, a demonic
        spirit claiming to foretell the future and discover hidden knowledge], and
        she brought her owners a good profit by fortune-telling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She followed after Paul and us and kept screaming and shouting, \u201CThese
        men are servants of the Most High God! They are proclaiming to you the way
        of salvation!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "She continued doing this for several days. Then Paul, being greatly
        annoyed and worn out, turned and said to the spirit [inside her], \u201CI
        command you in the name of Jesus Christ [as His representative] to come out
        of her!\u201D And it came out at that very moment.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when her owners saw that their hope of profit was gone, they
        seized Paul and Silas and dragged them before the authorities in the market
        place [where trials were held], '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and when they had brought them before the chief magistrates, they
        said, \u201CThese men, who are Jews, are throwing our city into confusion
        and causing trouble. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Paul and Silas Imprisoned'
      title: Paul and Silas Imprisoned
      number: 21
      content: "They are publicly teaching customs which are unlawful for us, as
        Romans, to accept or observe.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The crowd also joined in the attack against them, and the chief magistrates
        tore their robes off them and ordered that Paul and Silas be beaten with
        rods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After striking them many times [with the rods], they threw them into
        prison, commanding the jailer to guard them securely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He, having received such a [strict] command, threw them into the
        inner prison (dungeon) and fastened their feet in the stocks [in an agonizing
        position].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But about midnight when Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns
        of praise to God, and the prisoners were listening to them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "suddenly there was a great earthquake, so [powerful] that the very
        foundations of the prison were shaken and at once all the doors were opened
        and everyone\u2019s chains were unfastened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the jailer, shaken out of sleep, saw the prison doors open,
        he drew his sword and was about to kill himself, thinking that the prisoners
        had escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But Paul shouted, saying, \u201CDo not hurt yourself, we are all
        here!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the jailer called for torches and rushed in, and trembling with
        fear he fell down before Paul and Silas, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Jailer Converted'
      title: The Jailer Converted
      number: 30
      content: "and after he brought them out [of the inner prison], he said, \u201CSirs,
        what must I do to be saved?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And they answered, \u201CBelieve in the Lord Jesus [as your personal
        Savior and entrust yourself to Him] and you will be saved, you and your household
        [if they also believe].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they spoke the word of the Lord [concerning eternal salvation
        through faith in Christ] to him and to all who were in his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he took them that very hour of the night and washed their bloody
        wounds, and immediately he was baptized, he and all his household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then he brought them into his house and set food before them, and
        rejoiced greatly, since he had believed in God with his entire family [accepting
        with joy what had been made known to them about the Christ].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Now when day came, the chief magistrates sent their officers, saying,
        \u201CRelease those men.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And the jailer repeated the words to Paul, saying, \u201CThe chief
        magistrates have sent word to release you; so come out now and go in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Paul said to them, \u201CThey have beaten us in public without
        a trial, men who are Romans, and have thrown us into prison; and now they
        are sending us out secretly? No! Let them come here themselves and bring
        us out!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The officers reported this message to the chief magistrates, and
        when they heard that the prisoners were Romans, they were frightened; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'so they came [to the prison] and appealed to them [with apologies],
        and when they brought them out, they kept begging them to leave the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So they left the prison and went to Lydia\u2019s house; and when
        they had seen the brothers and sisters, they encouraged and comforted them,
        and left."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul at Thessalonica'
      title: Paul at Thessalonica
      number: 1
      content: '  Now after Paul and Silas had traveled through Amphipolis and Apollonia,
        they came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Paul entered the synagogue, as was his custom, and for three
        Sabbaths he engaged in discussion and friendly debate with them from the
        Scriptures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "explaining and pointing out [scriptural evidence] that it was necessary
        for the Christ to suffer and rise from the dead, and saying, \u201CThis Jesus,
        whom I am proclaiming to you, is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And some of them were persuaded to believe and joined Paul and Silas,
        along with a large number of the God-fearing Greeks and many of the leading
        women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But the [unbelieving] Jews became jealous, and taking along some
        thugs from [the lowlifes in] the market place, they formed a mob and set
        the city in an uproar; and then attacking Jason\u2019s house tried to bring
        Paul and Silas out to the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when they failed to find them, they dragged Jason and some brothers
        before the city authorities, shouting, \u201CThese men who have turned the
        world upside down have come here too; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and Jason has welcomed them [into his house and protected them]!
        And they all are saying things contrary to the decrees of Caesar, [actually]
        claiming that there is another king, Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They stirred up the crowd and the city authorities who heard these
        things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Paul at Berea'
      title: Paul at Berea
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they had taken security (bail) from Jason and the others,
        they let them go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The brothers immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to Berea;
        and when they arrived, they entered the Jewish synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now these people were more noble and open-minded than those in Thessalonica,
        so they received the message [of salvation through faith in the Christ] with
        great eagerness, examining the Scriptures daily to see if these things were
        so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As a result many of them became believers, together with a number
        of prominent Greek women and men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But when the Jews of Thessalonica learned that the word of God [concerning
        eternal salvation through faith in Christ] had also been preached by Paul
        at Berea, they came there too, agitating and disturbing the crowds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So at that time the brothers immediately sent Paul away to go as
        far as the sea; but Silas and Timothy remained there [at Berea]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Paul at Athens'
      title: Paul at Athens
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who escorted Paul brought him to Athens; and [after] receiving
        instructions [from Paul] for Silas and Timothy to join him as soon as possible,
        they left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now while Paul was waiting for them at Athens, his spirit was greatly
        angered when he saw that the city was full of idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So he had discussions in the synagogue with the Jews and the God-fearing
        Gentiles, and in the market place day after day with any who happened to
        be there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers began to engage
        in conversation with him. And some said, \u201CWhat could this idle babbler
        [with his eclectic, scrap-heap learning] have in mind to say?\u201D Others
        said, \u201CHe seems to be a proclaimer of strange deities\u201D\u2014because
        he was preaching the good news about Jesus and the resurrection. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They took him and brought him to the Areopagus (Hill of Ares, the
        Greek god of war), saying, \u201CMay we know what this [strange] new teaching
        is which you are proclaiming? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For you are bringing some startling and strange things to our ears;
        so we want to know what they mean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Sermon on Mars Hill'
      title: Sermon on Mars Hill
      number: 21
      content: '(Now all the Athenians and the foreigners visiting there used to
        spend their [leisure] time in nothing other than telling or hearing something
        new.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Paul, standing in the center of the Areopagus, said: \u201CMen
        of Athens, I observe [with every turn I make throughout the city] that you
        are very religious and devout in all respects. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now as I was going along and carefully looking at your objects of
        worship, I came to an altar with this inscription: \u2018TO AN UNKNOWN GOD.\u2019
        Therefore what you already worship as unknown, this I proclaim to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The God who created the world and everything in it, since He is Lord
        of heaven and earth, does not dwell in temples made with hands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'nor is He served by human hands, as though He needed anything, because
        it is He who gives to all [people] life and breath and all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And He made from one man every nation of mankind to live on the face
        of the earth, having determined their appointed times and the boundaries
        of their lands and territories. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This was so that they would seek God, if perhaps they might grasp
        for Him and find Him, though He is not far from each one of us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For in Him we live and move and exist [that is, in Him we actually
        have our being], as even some of your own poets have said, \u2018For we also
        are His children.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So then, being God\u2019s children, we should not think that the
        Divine Nature (deity) is like gold or silver or stone, an image formed by
        the art and imagination or skill of man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore God overlooked and disregarded the former ages of ignorance;
        but now He commands all people everywhere to repent [that is, to change their
        old way of thinking, to regret their past sins, and to seek God\u2019s purpose
        for their lives], "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "because He has set a day when He will judge the inhabited world in
        righteousness by a Man whom He has appointed and destined for that task,
        and He has provided credible proof to everyone by raising Him from the dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now when they heard [the term] resurrection from the dead, some mocked
        and sneered; but others said, \u201CWe will hear from you again about this
        matter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Paul left them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: But some men joined him and believed; among them were Dionysius, [a
        judge] of the Council of Areopagus, and a woman named Damaris, and others
        with them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul at Corinth'
      title: Paul at Corinth
      number: 1
      content: '  After this Paul left Athens and went to Corinth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There he met a Jew named Aquila, a native of Pontus, who had recently
        come from Italy with his wife, Priscilla, because [the Roman Emperor] Claudius
        had issued an edict that all the Jews were to leave Rome. Paul went to see
        them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and because he was of the same trade, he stayed with them; and they
        worked together for they were tent-makers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he reasoned and debated in the synagogue every Sabbath, trying
        to persuade Jews and Greeks;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but when Silas and Timothy came down from Macedonia (northern Greece),
        Paul began devoting himself completely to [preaching] the word, and solemnly
        testifying to the Jews that Jesus is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed). '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But since the Jews kept resisting and opposing him, and blaspheming
        [God], he shook out his robe and said to them, \u201CYour blood (damnation)
        be on your own heads! I am innocent of it. From now on I will go to the Gentiles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he moved on from there and went to the house of a man named
        Titius Justus, who worshiped God and whose house was next door to the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Crispus, the leader of the synagogue, believed in the Lord together
        with his entire household [joyfully acknowledging Him as Messiah and Savior];
        and many of the Corinthians who heard [Paul\u2019s message] were believing
        and being baptized. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "One night the Lord said to Paul in a vision, <JESUS>\u201CDo not
        be afraid anymore, but go on speaking and do not be silent;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>for I am with you, and no one will attack you in order to
        hurt you, because I have many people in this city.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So he settled there for a year and six months, teaching them the
        word of God [concerning eternal salvation through faith in Christ].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Gallio was proconsul of Achaia (southern Greece), the Jews
        made a united attack on Paul and brought him before the judgment seat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "declaring, \u201CThis man is persuading people to worship God in
        violation of the law [of Moses].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But when Paul was about to reply, Gallio said to the Jews, \u201CIf
        it were a matter of some misdemeanor or serious crime, O Jews, I would have
        reason to put up with you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but since it is merely a question [of doctrine within your religion]
        about words and names and your own law, see to it yourselves; I am unwilling
        to judge these matters.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he drove them away from the judgment seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the Greeks all seized Sosthenes, the leader of the synagogue,
        and began beating him right in front of the judgment seat; but Gallio paid
        no attention to any of this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Paul stayed for a while longer, and then told the brothers and sisters
        goodbye and sailed for Syria; and he was accompanied by Priscilla and Aquila.
        At Cenchrea [the southeastern port of Corinth] he had his hair cut, because
        he was keeping a [Nazirite] vow [of abstention]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they arrived in Ephesus, and he left the others there; but he
        entered the synagogue and reasoned and debated with the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they asked him to stay for a longer time, he refused; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but after telling them goodbye and saying, \u201CI will return again
        if God is willing,\u201D he set sail from Ephesus.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Paul\u2019s Third Missionary Journey"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Third Missionary Journey"
      number: 22
      content: 'When he had landed at Caesarea, he went up and greeted the church
        [at Jerusalem], and then went down to Antioch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After spending some time there, he left and traveled through the
        territory of Galatia and Phrygia, strengthening and encouraging all the disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now a Jew named Apollos, a native of Alexandria, came to Ephesus.
        He was an eloquent and cultured man, and well versed in the [Hebrew] Scriptures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'This man had been instructed in the way of the Lord, and being spiritually
        impassioned, he was speaking and teaching accurately the things about Jesus,
        though he knew only the baptism of John; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and he began to speak boldly and fearlessly in the synagogue. But
        when Priscilla and Aquila heard him, they took him aside and explained more
        accurately to him the way of God [and the full story of the life of Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when Apollos wanted to go across to Achaia (southern Greece),
        the brothers encouraged him and wrote to the disciples, [urging them] to
        welcome him gladly. When he arrived, he was a great help to those who, through
        grace, had believed and had followed Jesus as Lord and Savior, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: for he powerfully refuted the Jews in public discussions, proving
        by the Scriptures that Jesus is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul at Ephesus'
      title: Paul at Ephesus
      number: 1
      content: '  It happened that while Apollos was in Corinth, Paul went through
        the upper [inland] districts and came down to Ephesus, and found some disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He asked them, \u201CDid you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed
        [in Jesus as the Christ]?\u201D And they said, \u201CNo, we have not even
        heard that there is a Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he asked, \u201CInto what then were you baptized?\u201D They
        said, \u201CInto John\u2019s baptism.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Paul said, \u201CJohn performed a baptism of repentance, continually
        telling the people to believe in Him who was coming after him, that is, [to
        confidently accept and joyfully believe] in Jesus [the Messiah and Savior].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'After hearing this, they were baptized [again, this time] in the
        name of the Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Paul laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came on them,
        and they began speaking in [unknown] tongues (languages) and prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There were about twelve men in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he went into the synagogue and for three months spoke boldly,
        reasoning and arguing and persuading them about the kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But when some were becoming hardened and disobedient [to the word
        of God], discrediting and speaking evil of the Way (Jesus, Christianity)
        before the congregation, Paul left them, taking the disciples with him, and
        went on holding daily discussions in the lecture hall of Tyrannus [instead
        of in the synagogue]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Miracles at Ephesus'
      title: Miracles at Ephesus
      number: 10
      content: 'This continued for two years, so that all the inhabitants of [the
        west coast province of] Asia [Minor], Jews as well as Greeks, heard the word
        of the Lord [concerning eternal salvation through faith in Christ].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God was doing extraordinary and unusual miracles by the hands of
        Paul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that even handkerchiefs or face-towels or aprons that had touched
        his skin were brought to the sick, and their diseases left them and the evil
        spirits came out [of them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then some of the traveling Jewish exorcists also attempted to call
        the name of the Lord Jesus over those who had evil spirits, saying, \u201CI
        implore you and solemnly command you by the Jesus whom Paul preaches!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Seven sons of one [named] Sceva, a Jewish chief priest, were doing
        this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the evil spirit retorted, \u201CI know and recognize and acknowledge
        Jesus, and I know about Paul, but as for you, who are you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the man, in whom was the evil spirit, leaped on them and subdued
        all of them and overpowered them, so that they ran out of that house [in
        terror, stripped] naked and wounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'This became known to all who lived in Ephesus, both Jews and Greeks.
        And fear fell upon them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified
        and exalted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Many of those who had become believers were coming, confessing and
        disclosing their [former sinful] practices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And many of those who had practiced magical arts collected their
        books and [throwing book after book on the pile] began burning them in front
        of everyone. They calculated their value and found it to be 50,000 pieces
        of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the word of the Lord [concerning eternal salvation through faith
        in Christ] was growing greatly and prevailing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now after these events, Paul determined in the Spirit that he would
        travel through Macedonia and Achaia (most of the Greek mainland), and go
        to Jerusalem, saying, \u201CAfter I have been there, I must also see Rome
        [and preach the good news of salvation].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And after sending two of his assistants, Timothy and Erastus, to
        Macedonia [ahead of him], he stayed on in [the west coast province of] Asia
        [Minor] for a while.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'About that time there occurred no small disturbance concerning the
        Way (Jesus, Christianity). '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now a man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines
        of [the goddess] Artemis (Diana), was bringing no small profit to the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "These [craftsmen] he called together, along with the workmen of similar
        trades, and said, \u201CMen, you are well aware that we make a good living
        from this business. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You see and hear that not only at Ephesus, but almost all over [the
        province of] Asia, this Paul has persuaded [people to believe his teaching]
        and has misled a large number of people, claiming that gods made by [human]
        hands are not really gods at all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Not only is there danger that this trade of ours will be discredited,
        but also that the [magnificent] temple of the great goddess Artemis will
        be discredited, and that she whom all Asia and the world worship will even
        be dethroned and lose her glorious magnificence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When they heard this, they were filled with rage, and they began
        shouting, \u201CGreat is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the city was filled with confusion; and people rushed together
        [as a group] into the amphitheater, dragging along with them Gaius and Aristarchus,
        Macedonians who were Paul\u2019s traveling companions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Paul wanted to go into the [pagan] assembly, but the disciples would
        not let him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Even some of the Asiarchs (officials) who were his friends sent word
        to him and repeatedly warned him not to venture into the amphitheater. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now some shouted one thing and some another, for the gathering was
        in confusion and most of the people did not know why they had come together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Some of the crowd advised Alexander [to speak], since the Jews had
        pushed him forward; and Alexander motioned with his hand [for attention]
        and intended to make a defense to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But when they realized that he was a Jew, a single outcry went up
        from the crowd as they shouted for about two hours, \u201CGreat is Artemis
        of the Ephesians!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "After the town clerk had quieted the crowd, he said, \u201CMen of
        Ephesus, what person is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians
        is the guardian of the temple of the great Artemis and of that [sacred stone
        image of her] which fell from the sky? "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So, since these things cannot be denied, you ought to be quiet and
        stay calm and not do anything rash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For you have brought these men here who are neither temple robbers
        nor blasphemers of our goddess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So then, if Demetrius and the craftsmen who are with him have a complaint
        against anyone, the courts are in session and proconsuls are available; let
        them bring charges against one another there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But if you want anything beyond this, it will be settled in the lawful
        assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For we are running the risk of being accused of rioting in regard
        to today\u2019s events, and since there is no reason for it, we will be unable
        to give an account and justify this disorderly gathering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And when he had said these things, he dismissed the assembly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul in Macedonia and Greece'
      title: Paul in Macedonia and Greece
      number: 1
      content: '  After the uproar had ended, Paul sent for the disciples, and when
        he had encouraged them he told them goodbye, and set off to go to Macedonia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'After he had gone through those districts and had encouraged the
        believers, he came to Greece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he stayed three months, and when a plot was formed against him
        by the Jews as he was about to set sail for Syria, he decided to return through
        Macedonia (northern Greece). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He was accompanied by Sopater of Berea, the son of Pyrrhus, and by
        Aristarchus and Secundus of the Thessalonians, and by Gaius of Derbe, and
        Timothy, and Tychicus and Trophimus of Asia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'These men went on ahead and were waiting for us (including Luke)
        at Troas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We sailed from Philippi after the days of Unleavened Bread (Passover
        week), and within five days we reached them at Troas, where we stayed for
        seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now on the first day of the week (Sunday), when we were gathered
        together to break bread (share communion), Paul began talking with them,
        intending to leave the next day; and he kept on with his message until midnight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now there were many lamps in the upper room where we were assembled, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and there was a young man named Eutychus (\u201CLucky\u201D) sitting
        on the window sill. He was sinking into a deep sleep, and as Paul kept on
        talking longer and longer, he was completely overcome by sleep and fell down
        from the third story; and he was picked up dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Paul went down and threw himself on him and embraced him, and
        said [to those standing around him], \u201CDo not be troubled, because he
        is alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When Paul had gone back upstairs and had broken the bread and eaten,
        he talked [informally and confidentially] with them for a long time\u2014until
        daybreak [in fact]\u2014and then he left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Troas to Miletus'
      title: Troas to Miletus
      number: 12
      content: 'They took the boy [Eutychus] home alive, and were greatly comforted
        and encouraged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But we went on ahead to the ship and set sail for Assos, intending
        to take Paul on board there; for that was what he had arranged, intending
        himself to go [a shorter route] by land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So when he met us at Assos, we took him on board and sailed on to
        Mitylene. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Sailing from there, we arrived the next day [at a point] opposite
        Chios; the following day we crossed over to Samos, and the next day we arrived
        at Miletus [about 30 miles south of Ephesus]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Farewell to Ephesus'
      title: Farewell to Ephesus
      number: 16
      content: 'Paul had decided to sail on past Ephesus so that he would not end
        up spending time [unnecessarily] in [the province of] Asia (modern Turkey);
        for he was in a hurry to be in Jerusalem, if possible, on the day of Pentecost.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'However, from Miletus he sent word to Ephesus and summoned the elders
        of the church [to meet him there]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when they arrived he said to them:\u201CYou know well how I [lived
        when I] was with you, from the first day that I set foot in Asia [until now], "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'serving the Lord with all humility and with tears and trials which
        came on me because of the plots of the Jews [against me]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '[you know] how I did not shrink back in fear from telling you anything
        that was for your benefit, or from teaching you in public meetings, and from
        house to house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'solemnly [and wholeheartedly] testifying to both Jews and Greeks,
        urging them to turn in repentance to God and [to have] faith in our Lord
        Jesus Christ [for salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And now, compelled by the Spirit and obligated by my convictions,
        I am going to Jerusalem, not knowing what will happen to me there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'except that the Holy Spirit solemnly [and emphatically] affirms to
        me in city after city that imprisonment and suffering await me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But I do not consider my life as something of value or dear to me,
        so that I may [with joy] finish my course and the ministry which I received
        from the Lord Jesus, to testify faithfully of the good news of God\u2019s
        [precious, undeserved] grace [which makes us free of the guilt of sin and
        grants us eternal life].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd now, listen carefully: I know that none of you, among whom
        I went about preaching the kingdom, will see me again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For that reason I testify to you on this [our parting] day that I
        am innocent of the blood of all people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I did not shrink from declaring to you the whole purpose and
        plan of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Take care and be on guard for yourselves and for the whole flock
        over which the Holy Spirit has appointed you as overseers, to shepherd (tend,
        feed, guide) the church of God which He bought with His own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I know that after I am gone, [false teachers like] ferocious wolves
        will come in among you, not sparing the flock; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'even from among your own selves men will arise, speaking perverse
        and distorted things, to draw away the disciples after themselves [as their
        followers]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore be continually alert, remembering that for three years,
        night or day, I did not stop admonishing and advising each one [of you] with
        tears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And now I commend you to God [placing you in His protective, loving
        care] and [I commend you] to the word of His grace [the counsel and promises
        of His unmerited favor]. His grace is able to build you up and to give you
        the [rightful] inheritance among all those who are sanctified [that is, among
        those who are set apart for God\u2019s purpose\u2014all believers]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I had no desire for anyone\u2019s silver or gold or [expensive] clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You know personally that these hands ministered to my own needs [working
        in manual labor] and to [those of] the people who were with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "In everything I showed you [by example] that by working hard in this
        way you must help the weak and remember the words of the Lord Jesus, that
        He Himself said, <JESUS>\u2018It is more blessed</JESUS> [and brings greater
        joy] <JESUS>to give than to receive.\u2019\u2009\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'When he had said these things, he knelt down and prayed with them
        all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And they began to weep openly and threw their arms around Paul\u2019s
        neck, and repeatedly kissed him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: grieving and distressed especially over the word which he had spoken,
        that they would not see him again. And they accompanied him to the ship.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Sails from Miletus'
      title: Paul Sails from Miletus
      number: 1
      content: '  When we had torn ourselves away from them and set sail, we ran
        a straight course and came to Cos, and on the next day to Rhodes, and from
        there to Patara; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and after finding a ship crossing over to Phoenicia, we went on board
        and set sail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'After we came in sight of Cyprus, leaving it on our left (port side),
        we sailed on to Syria and put in at Tyre; for there the ship was to unload
        her cargo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After looking up the disciples [in Tyre], we stayed there [with them]
        seven days; and they kept telling Paul through the [Holy] Spirit not to set
        foot in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When our days there came to an end, we left and proceeded on our
        journey, while all of the disciples, with their wives and children, escorted
        us on our way until we were outside the city. After kneeling down on the
        beach and praying, we told one another goodbye. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then we boarded the ship, and they returned to their homes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When we had completed the voyage from Tyre, we landed [twenty miles
        to the south] at Ptolemais, and after greeting the believers, we stayed with
        them for one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'On the next day we left and came to Caesarea, and we went to the
        house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven [deacons], and stayed
        with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He had four virgin daughters who had the gift of prophecy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As we were staying there for some time, a prophet named Agabus came
        down from Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And coming to [see] us, he took Paul\u2019s [wide] band (belt, sash)
        and bound his own feet and hands, and said, \u201CThis is what the Holy Spirit
        says: \u2018In this same way the Jews in Jerusalem will bind the man who
        owns this band, and they will hand him over to the Gentiles (pagans).\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when we had heard this, both we and the local residents began
        pleading with Paul trying to persuade him not to go up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Paul replied, \u201CWhat are you doing, weeping and breaking
        my heart [like this]? For I am ready not only to be bound and imprisoned,
        but even to die at Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Paul at Jerusalem'
      title: Paul at Jerusalem
      number: 14
      content: "And since he would not be dissuaded, we stopped pleading and fell
        silent, saying, \u201CThe Lord\u2019s will be done!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'After this we got ready and started on our way up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Some of the disciples from Caesarea also came with us, taking us
        to [the house of] Mnason, a man from Cyprus, a disciple of long standing
        with whom we were to lodge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When we arrived in Jerusalem, the brothers and sisters welcomed us
        gladly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'On the next day Paul went with us to [see] James, and all the elders
        of the church were present. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After greeting them, Paul began to give a detailed account of the
        things that God had done among the Gentiles through his ministry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when they heard it, they began glorifying and praising God; and
        they said to him, \u201CYou see, brother, how many thousands of believers
        there are among the Jews, and they are all enthusiastic supporters of the
        Law [of Moses]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now they have been told about you, that you are teaching all the
        Jews who are living among the Gentiles to turn away from [the Law of] Moses,
        advising them not to circumcise their children or to live according to the
        [Mosaic] customs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'What then should be done? They will certainly hear that you have
        arrived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Therefore do just what we tell you. We have four men who have taken
        a vow; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'take these men and purify yourself along with them, and pay their
        expenses [for the temple offerings] so that they may shave their heads. Then
        everyone will know that there is nothing to the things they have been told
        about you, but that you yourself also follow and keep the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But with regard to the Gentiles who have believed [in Christ], we
        have sent them a letter with our decision that they should abstain from meat
        sacrificed to idols and from [consuming] blood and from [the meat of] what
        has been strangled and from sexual immorality.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Paul Seized in the Temple'
      title: Paul Seized in the Temple
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Paul took the [four] men, and the next day he purified himself
        along with them [by submitting to the ritual]. He went into the temple to
        give notice of [the time] when the days of purification [ending each vow]
        would be fulfilled and the usual offering could be presented on behalf of
        each one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the seven days [required to complete the ritual] were almost
        over, [some] Jews from [the province of] Asia [Minor], caught sight of him
        in the temple, and began to stir up the crowd, and they seized him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "shouting, \u201CMen of Israel, help us! This is the man who teaches
        all men everywhere against our people and the Law and this place. And besides,
        he has brought Greeks into the temple and has defiled this holy place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For they had previously seen Trophimus the Ephesian in the city with
        Paul, and they assumed that he had brought the man into the temple [beyond
        the court of the Gentiles]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the whole city was provoked and confused, and the people rushed
        together. They seized Paul and dragged him out of the temple, and immediately
        the gates were closed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now while they were trying to kill him, word came to the commander
        of the [Roman] garrison that all Jerusalem was in a state of upheaval. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So he immediately took soldiers and centurions and ran down among
        them. When the people saw the commander and the soldiers, they stopped beating
        Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the commander came up and arrested Paul, and ordered that he
        be bound with two chains. Then he asked who he was and what he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But some in the crowd were shouting one thing and others something
        else; and since he could not determine the facts because of the uproar, he
        ordered that Paul be taken to the barracks [in the tower of Antonia]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When Paul got to the steps, he was carried by the soldiers because
        of the violence of the mob; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "for the majority of the people kept following them, shouting, \u201CAway
        with him! [Kill him!]\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Just as Paul was about to be taken into the barracks, he asked the
        commander, \u201CMay I say something to you?\u201D And the man replied, \u201CDo
        you know Greek? "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then you are not [as I assumed] the Egyptian who some time ago stirred
        up a rebellion and led those 4,000 men of the Assassins out into the wilderness?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Paul said, \u201CI am a Jew from Tarsus in Cilicia (Mersin Province,
        Turkey), a citizen of no insignificant city; and I beg you, allow me to speak
        to the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: When the commander had given him permission, Paul, standing on the
        steps, gestured with his hand to the people; and when there was a great hush,
        he spoke to them in the Hebrew dialect (Jewish Aramaic), saying,
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Defense before the Jews"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Defense before the Jews"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBrethren and fathers (kinsmen), hear my defense which I now
        offer to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When they heard that he was addressing them in the Hebrew dialect,
        they became even more quiet. And he continued,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI am a Jew, born in Tarsus of Cilicia, but brought up in this
        city, educated at the feet of Gamaliel according to the strictness of the
        law of our fathers, being ardent and passionate for God just as all of you
        are today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I persecuted and pursued the followers of this Way to the death,
        binding them with chains and putting [followers of Jesus] both men and women
        into prisons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'as the high priest and all the Council of the elders (Sanhedrin,
        Jewish High Court) can testify; because from them I received letters to the
        brothers, and I was on my way to Damascus in order to bring those [believers]
        who were there to Jerusalem in chains to be punished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBut as I was on my way, approaching Damascus about noontime,
        a great blaze of light suddenly flashed from heaven and shone around me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Saul,
        Saul, why are you persecuting Me?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I replied, \u2018Who are You, Lord?\u2019 And He said to me,
        <JESUS>\u2018I am Jesus the Nazarene, whom you are persecuting.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now those who were with me saw the light, but did not understand
        the voice of the One who was speaking to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I asked, \u2018What shall I do, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord answered
        me, <JESUS>\u2018Get up and go into Damascus. There you will be told all
        that is appointed </JESUS>and destined for you to do.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But since I could not see because of the [glorious intensity and
        dazzling] brightness of that light, I was led by the hand by those who were
        with me and came into Damascus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd one Ananias, a devout man according to the standard of
        the Law, and well spoken of by all the Jews who lived there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "came to [see] me, and standing near, he said to me, \u2018Brother
        Saul, receive your sight!\u2019 And at that very moment I [recovered my sight
        and] looked up at him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u2018The God of our fathers has appointed you to know
        His will, [and to progressively understand His plan with clarity and power]
        and to see the Righteous One [Jesus Christ, the Messiah] and to hear a message
        from His [own] mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For you will be His witness to all men testifying of what you have
        seen and heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now, why do you delay? Get up and be baptized, and wash away your
        sins by calling on His name [for salvation].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThen it happened when I had returned to Jerusalem and was praying
        in the temple [enclosure], that I fell into a trance (vision); "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and I saw Him saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Hurry and get out of Jerusalem
        quickly, because they will not accept your testimony about Me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And I said, \u2018Lord, they themselves know [without any doubt]
        that in one synagogue after another I used to imprison and beat those who
        believed in You [and Your message of salvation]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when the blood of Your witness Stephen was being shed, I also
        was standing nearby approving and consenting [to his death], and guarding
        the coats of those who were killing him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the Lord said to me, <JESUS>\u2018Go, I will send you far away
        to the Gentiles.\u2019\u2009\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "They listened to Paul until [he made] this [last] statement, but
        now they raised their voices and shouted, \u201CAway with such a man from
        the earth! He is not fit to live!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And as they were shouting and throwing off their coats [getting ready
        to stone Paul] and tossing dust into the air [expressing their anger], '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the commander ordered him to be brought into the barracks, stating
        that he was to be interrogated with a whip in order to learn why the people
        were shouting against him that way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But when they had stretched him out with the leather straps [in preparation
        for the whip], Paul said to the centurion who was standing by, \u201CIs it
        legal for you to whip a man who is a Roman citizen and uncondemned [without
        a trial]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the centurion heard this, he went to the commander and said
        to him, \u201CWhat are you about to do? This man is a Roman!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So the commander came and asked Paul, \u201CTell me, are you a Roman?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CYes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The commander replied, \u201CI purchased this citizenship [of mine]
        for a large sum of money [so how did you acquire yours?].\u201D Paul said,
        \u201CBut I was actually born a citizen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So those who were about to interrogate him by torture immediately
        let him go; and the commander was also afraid when he realized that Paul
        was a Roman and he had put him in chains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But on the next day, wanting to know the real reason why Paul was
        being accused by the Jews, he released him and ordered the chief priests
        and the whole Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court) to assemble; and brought
        Paul down and presented him before them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul before the Council'
      title: Paul before the Council
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Paul, looking intently at the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High
        Court), said, \u201CKinsmen, I have lived my life before God with a perfectly
        good conscience until this very day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '[At this] the high priest Ananias ordered those who stood beside
        him to strike Paul on the mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Paul said to him, \u201CGod is going to strike you, you whitewashed
        wall! Do you actually sit to judge me according to the Law, and yet in violation
        of the Law order me to be struck?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But those who stood near Paul said, \u201CAre you insulting the high
        priest of God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Paul said, \u201CI was not aware, brothers, that he was high priest;
        for it is written, \u2018You shall not speak evil of a ruler of your people.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But recognizing that one group were Sadducees and the other Pharisees,
        Paul began affirming loudly in the Council chamber, \u201CKinsmen, I am a
        Pharisee, a son of Pharisees; I am on trial for the hope and resurrection
        of the dead!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When he said this, an angry dispute erupted between the Pharisees
        and the Sadducees, and the [whole crowded] assembly was divided [into two
        factions]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the Sadducees say that there is no [such thing as a] resurrection,
        nor an angel, nor a spirit, but the Pharisees [speak out freely and] acknowledge
        [their belief in] them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then a great uproar occurred, and some of the scribes of the Pharisees\u2019
        party stood up and began to argue heatedly [in Paul\u2019s favor], saying,
        \u201CWe find nothing wrong with this man; suppose a spirit or an angel has
        [really] spoken to him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And as the dissension became even greater, the commander, fearing
        that Paul would be torn to pieces by them, ordered the troops to go down
        and forcibly take him from them, and bring him to the barracks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Conspiracy to Kill Paul'
      title: A Conspiracy to Kill Paul
      number: 11
      content: "On the following night the Lord stood near Paul and said, <JESUS>\u201CBe
        brave; for as you have solemnly </JESUS>and faithfully witnessed about Me
        at Jerusalem, so you must also testify at Rome.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when day came, the Jews formed a conspiracy and bound themselves
        under an oath (curse), saying that they would not eat or drink until they
        had killed Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There were more than forty [men] who formed this plot [and swore
        this oath]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They went to the chief priests and elders and said, \u201CWe have
        bound ourselves under a solemn oath not to taste anything [neither food nor
        drink] until we have killed Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So now you, along with the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court),
        notify the commander to bring Paul down to you, as if you were going to investigate
        his case more thoroughly. But we are ready to kill him before he comes near
        [the place].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But the son of Paul\u2019s sister heard of their [planned] ambush,
        and he went to the barracks and told Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Paul, calling in one of the centurions, said, \u201CTake this
        young man to the commander, for he has something to tell him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he took him and led him to the commander and said, \u201CPaul
        the prisoner called for me and asked me to bring this young man to you, because
        he has something to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The commander took him by the hand and stepping aside, began to ask
        him privately, \u201CWhat is it that you have to tell me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said, \u201CThe Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul
        down to the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court) tomorrow, as if they were
        going to interrogate him more thoroughly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But do not listen to them, for more than forty of them are lying
        in wait for him, and they have bound themselves with an oath not to eat or
        drink until they have killed him. Even now they are ready, just waiting for
        your promise.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Paul Moved to Caesarea Maritima'
      title: Paul Moved to Caesarea Maritima
      number: 22
      content: "So the commander let the young man leave, instructing him, \u201CDo
        not tell anyone that you have given me this information.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then summoning two of the centurions, he said, \u201CHave two hundred
        soldiers ready by the third hour of the night (9:00 p.m.) to go as far as
        Caesarea, with seventy horsemen and two hundred spearmen; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "also provide mounts for Paul to ride, and bring him safely to Felix
        the governor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And [after instructing the centurions] he wrote a letter to this
        effect:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CClaudius Lysias, to the most excellent governor Felix, greetings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This man was seized [as a prisoner] by the Jews and was about to
        be killed by them, when I came upon him with the troops and rescued him,
        having learned that he was a Roman citizen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And wanting to know the exact charge which they were making against
        him, I brought him down to their Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court);  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and I discovered that he was accused in regard to questions and issues
        in their Law, but [he was] under no accusation that would call for the penalty
        of death or [even] for imprisonment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When I was told that there would be a plot against the man, I sent
        him to you immediately, also directing his accusers to bring their charges
        against him before you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the soldiers, in compliance with their orders, took Paul and brought
        him to Antipatris during the night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the next day, leaving the horsemen to go on with him, they returned
        to the barracks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When these [horsemen] reached Caesarea, they delivered the letter
        to the governor, and also presented Paul to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'After reading the letter, he asked which province Paul was from,
        and when he learned that he was from Cilicia [an imperial province], '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "he said, \u201CI will hear your case when your accusers have arrived,\u201D
        giving orders that Paul be kept under guard in Herod\u2019s Praetorium (the
        governor\u2019s official residence)."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul before Felix'
      title: Paul before Felix
      number: 1
      content: '  Five days later, the high priest Ananias came down [from Jerusalem
        to Caesarea] with some elders and an attorney named Tertullus [acting as
        spokesman and counsel]. They presented to the governor their [formal] charges
        against Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "After Paul had been summoned, Tertullus began the complaint [against
        him], saying to the governor:\u201CSince through you we have attained great
        peace, and since by your foresight reforms are being carried out for this
        nation, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'in every way and in every place, most excellent Felix, we acknowledge
        this with all gratitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But so that I do not weary you further, I beg you to grant us, by
        your kindness, a brief hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For we have found this man to be a public menace and one who instigates
        dissension among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the
        [heretical] sect of the Nazarenes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He even tried to desecrate the temple, but we took him into custody
        [and we intended to judge him by our Law, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but Lysias the commander came, and with great force took him out
        of our hands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and ordered his accusers to come before you.] By interrogating him
        yourself concerning all these matters you will be able to determine [the
        truth about] these things with which we charge him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Jews also joined in the attack, declaring and insisting that
        these things were so.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the governor nodded for him to speak, Paul answered,\u201CKnowing
        that for many years you have been a judge over this nation, I make my defense
        cheerfully and with good courage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As you can easily verify, it has been no more than twelve days since
        I went up to Jerusalem to worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Neither in the temple, nor in the synagogues, nor elsewhere in the
        city did they find me carrying on a discussion or disputing with anybody
        or causing a crowd to gather. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Nor can they present evidence to you to prove what they now bring
        against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But I confess this to you, that according to the Way, which they
        call a [divisive and heretical] sect, I do worship and serve the God of our
        fathers, [confidently] believing everything that is in accordance with the
        Law [of Moses] and that is written in the Prophets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'having [the same] hope in God which these men cherish themselves,
        that there shall certainly be a resurrection of [the dead], both of the righteous
        and of the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In view of this, I also do my best and strive always to have a clear
        conscience before God and before men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now after several years I came [to Jerusalem] to bring to my people
        charitable contributions and offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They found me in the temple presenting these offerings, after I had
        undergone [the rites of] purification, without any crowd or uproar. But there
        were some Jews from [the west coast province of] Asia [Minor], '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'who ought to have been here before you to present their charges,
        if they have anything against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Or else let these men tell what crime they found [me guilty of] when
        I stood before the Council (Sanhedrin, Jewish High Court), '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "other than for this one statement which I had shouted out as I stood
        among them, \u2018For the resurrection of the dead I am on trial before you
        today.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Felix, having a rather accurate understanding about the Way,
        put them off, saying, \u201CWhen Lysias the commander comes down, I will
        decide your case.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he ordered the centurion to keep Paul in custody, but to let
        him have some freedom, and [he told the centurion] not to stop any of his
        friends from providing for his needs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Several days later Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who was a Jewess.
        He sent for Paul and listened to him talk about faith in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But as he was discussing righteousness, self-control [honorable behavior,
        personal integrity], and the judgment to come, Felix became frightened and
        said, \u201CGo away for now, and when I find [a convenient] time I will send
        for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'At the same time he was also hoping to get money from Paul [as a
        bribe]; so he continued to send for him quite often and talked with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: But after two years had passed, Felix was succeeded [in office] by
        Porcius Festus; and wishing to do the Jews a favor, Felix left Paul imprisoned.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul before Festus'
      title: Paul before Festus
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Festus arrived in the province, and three days later he went
        up to Jerusalem from Caesarea [Maritima]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And [there in Jerusalem] the chief priests and the leading men of
        the Jews brought charges against Paul [before Festus], and they repeatedly
        pleaded with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'asking as a concession against Paul, that he would have him brought
        to Jerusalem; (meanwhile planning an ambush to kill him on the way). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Festus answered that Paul was being held in custody in Caesarea [Maritima]
        and that he himself was about to leave shortly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSo,\u201D he said, \u201Clet those who are in a position of
        authority among you go there with me, and if there is anything criminal about
        the man, let them bring charges against him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now after Festus had spent no more than eight or ten days among them,
        he went down to Caesarea, and on the next day he took his seat on the tribunal
        (the judicial bench), and ordered Paul to be brought [before him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After Paul arrived, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood
        around him, bringing many serious charges against him which they were not
        able to prove, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "while Paul declared in his own defense, \u201CI have done no wrong
        and committed no offense either against the Law of the Jews or against the
        temple or against Caesar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Festus, wishing to do the Jews a favor, answered Paul, \u201CAre
        you willing to go up to Jerusalem and stand trial there in my presence [before
        the Jewish Sanhedrin] on these charges?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Paul said, \u201CI am standing before Caesar\u2019s tribunal, where
        I ought to be tried. I have done nothing wrong to the Jews, as you also very
        well know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore, if I am guilty and have committed anything worthy of death,
        I do not try to escape death; but if there is nothing to the accusations
        which these men are bringing against me, no one can hand me over to them.
        I appeal to Caesar (Emperor Nero).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Festus, after conferring with [the men who formed] his council,
        answered, \u201CYou have appealed to Caesar; to Caesar you shall go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now several days later, Agrippa [II] the king and Bernice [his sister]
        arrived at Caesarea and paid their respects to Festus [the new governor]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "While they were spending many days there, Festus laid Paul\u2019s
        case before the king, saying, \u201CThere is a man here who was left as a
        prisoner by Felix. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When I was at Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of the
        Jews [told me about him and] brought charges against him, petitioning for
        a sentence of condemnation against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I told them that it was not the custom of the Romans to hand over
        any man [for punishment] before the accused meets his accusers face to face
        and has the opportunity to defend himself against the charges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So after they arrived together here, I did not delay, but on the
        next day took my place on the tribunal and ordered that the man be brought
        before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When his accusers stood up, they brought no charges against him of
        crimes that I was expecting [neither civil nor criminal actions], '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'instead they had some points of disagreement with him about their
        own religion and about one Jesus, a man who had died, but whom Paul kept
        asserting and insisting [over and over] to be alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And I, being at a loss as to how to investigate these things, asked
        whether he was willing to go to Jerusalem and be tried there regarding these
        matters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Paul appealed to be held in custody for a decision by the
        Emperor [Nero], I ordered him to be kept in custody until I could send him
        to Caesar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Paul before Agrippa'
      title: Paul before Agrippa
      number: 22
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CI would like to hear the man myself.\u201D
        \u201CTomorrow,\u201D Festus replied, \u201Cyou will hear him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the next day Agrippa and [his sister] Bernice came with great
        pageantry, and they went into the auditorium accompanied by the military
        commanders and the prominent men of the city. At the command of Festus, Paul
        was brought in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Festus said, \u201CKing Agrippa and all you gentlemen present
        with us, you see this man [Paul] about whom all the Jewish people appealed
        to me, both at Jerusalem and here, loudly insisting that he ought not to
        live any longer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But I found that he had done nothing worthy of death; however, since
        he appealed to the Emperor [Nero], I decided to send him [to Rome]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But I have nothing specific about him to write to my lord. So I have
        brought him before all of you, and especially before you, King Agrippa, so
        that after the investigation has taken place, I will have something to put
        in writing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For it seems absurd and unreasonable to me to send a prisoner [to
        Rome] without indicating the charges against him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Defense before Agrippa"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Defense before Agrippa"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CYou are [now] permitted to speak
        on your own behalf.\u201D At that, Paul stretched out his hand [as an orator]
        and made his defense [as follows]:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI consider myself fortunate, King Agrippa, since it is before
        you that I am to make my defense today regarding all the charges brought
        against me by the Jews, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'especially because you are an expert [fully knowledgeable, experienced
        and unusually conversant] in all the Jewish customs and controversial issues;
        therefore, I beg you to listen to me patiently.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CSo then, all the Jews know my manner of life from my youth
        up, which from the beginning was spent among my own nation [the Jewish people],
        and in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have known me for a long time, if they are willing to testify
        to it, that according to the strictest sect of our religion, I have lived
        as a Pharisee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now I am standing trial for the hope of the promise made by God
        to our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Which hope [of the Messiah and the resurrection] our twelve tribes
        [confidently] expect to realize as they serve and worship God in earnest
        night and day. And for this hope, O King, I am being accused by Jews! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Why is it thought incredible by [any of] you that God raises the
        dead?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSo then, I [once] thought to myself that it was my duty to
        do many things in opposition to the name of Jesus of Nazareth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And this is just what I did in Jerusalem; I not only locked up many
        of the saints (God\u2019s people) in prison after receiving authority from
        the chief priests, but also when they were being condemned to death, I cast
        my vote against them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I often punished them [making them suffer] in all the synagogues
        and tried to force them to blaspheme; and in my extreme rage at them, I kept
        hunting them even to foreign cities [harassing and persecuting them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhile so engaged, as I was traveling to Damascus with the authority
        and commission and full power of the chief priests, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'at midday, O King, I saw on the way a light from heaven surpassing
        the brightness of the sun, shining all around me and those who were traveling
        with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when we all had fallen to the ground, I heard a voice in the
        Hebrew dialect (Jewish Aramaic) saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Saul, Saul, why
        are you persecuting Me? </JESUS><JESUS>It is hard for you to kick</JESUS>
        [repeatedly] <JESUS>against the </JESUS><JESUS>goads</JESUS> [offering pointless
        resistance].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I said, \u2018Who are You, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said, <JESUS>\u2018I
        am Jesus whom you are persecuting.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>Get up and stand on your feet. I have appeared to you for
        this purpose, to appoint you</JESUS> [to serve] <JESUS>as a minister and
        as a witness</JESUS> [to testify, with authority,] <JESUS>not only to the
        things which you have seen, but also to the things in which I will appear
        to you,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '[choosing you for Myself and] <JESUS>rescuing you from the </JESUS>Jewish
        people and from the Gentiles, to whom I am sending you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>to open their</JESUS> [spiritual] <JESUS>eyes so that they
        may turn from darkness to light and from the power of Satan to God, that
        they may receive forgiveness </JESUS>and release from their sins and an inheritance
        among those who have been sanctified (set apart, made holy) by faith in Me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CSo, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "but I openly proclaimed first to those at Damascus, then at Jerusalem
        and throughout the region of Judea, and even to the Gentiles, that they should
        repent [change their inner self\u2014their old way of thinking] and turn
        to God, doing deeds and living lives which are consistent with repentance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Because of this some Jews seized me in the temple and tried to kill
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But I have had help from God to this day, and I stand [before people]
        testifying to small and great alike, stating nothing except what the Prophets
        and Moses said would come to pass\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed) was to suffer, and that
        He by being the first to rise from the dead [with an incorruptible body]
        would proclaim light (salvation) both to the Jewish people and to the Gentiles.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "While Paul was making this defense, Festus said loudly, \u201CPaul,
        you are out of your mind! Your great education is turning you toward madness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Paul replied, \u201CI am not out of my mind, most excellent and
        noble Festus, but [with a sound mind] I am uttering rational words of truth
        and reason. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For [your majesty] the king understands these things, and [therefore]
        I am also speaking to him with confidence and boldness, since I am convinced
        that none of these things escape his notice; for this has not been done in
        a corner [hidden from view, in secret]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "King Agrippa, do you believe the [writings of the] Prophets [their
        messages and words]? I know that you do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CIn a short time [and with so little
        effort] you [almost] persuade me to become a Christian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Paul replied, \u201CWhether in a short time or long, I wish to
        God that not only you, but also all who hear me today, might become such
        as I am, except for these chains.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the king stood up, and [with him] the governor and Bernice,
        and those who were sitting with them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and after they had gone out, they began saying to one another, \u201CThis
        man is not doing anything worthy of death or [even] of imprisonment.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CThis man could have been set free
        if he had not appealed to Caesar (Emperor Nero).\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Is Sent to Rome'
      title: Paul Is Sent to Rome
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when it was determined that we (including Luke) would sail
        for Italy, they turned Paul and some other prisoners over to a centurion
        of the Augustan Regiment named Julius. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And going aboard a ship from Adramyttian which was about to sail
        for the ports along the [west] coast [province] of Asia [Minor], we put out
        to sea; and Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica, accompanied us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The next day we landed at Sidon; and Julius, treating Paul with [thoughtful]
        consideration, allowed him to go to his friends there and be cared for and
        refreshed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From there we put out to sea and sailed to the leeward (sheltered)
        side of Cyprus [for protection from weather] because the winds were against
        us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When we had sailed across the sea along the coasts of Cilicia and
        Pamphylia, we landed at Myra in Lycia [on the south coast of Asia Minor]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There the centurion [Julius] found an Alexandrian ship [a grain ship
        of the Roman fleet] sailing for Italy, and he put us aboard it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For a number of days we sailed slowly and arrived with difficulty
        off Cnidus; then, because the wind did not allow us to go farther, we sailed
        under the leeward (sheltered) side of Crete, off Salmone; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and hugging the shore with difficulty, we came to a place called
        Fair Havens, near the city of Lasea [on the south side of Crete].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now much time had been lost, and navigation was dangerous, because
        even [the time for] the fast (Day of Atonement) was already over, so Paul
        began to strongly warn them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "saying, \u201CMen, I sense [after careful thought and observation]
        that this voyage will certainly be a disaster and with great loss, not only
        of the cargo and the ship, but also of our lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'However, the centurion [Julius, ranking officer on board] was persuaded
        by the pilot and the owner of the ship rather than by what Paul said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Because the harbor was not well situated for wintering, the majority
        [of the sailors] decided to put to sea from there, hoping somehow to reach
        Phoenix, a harbor of Crete facing southwest and northwest, and spend the
        winter there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Shipwreck'
      title: Shipwreck
      number: 13
      content: 'So when the south wind blew softly, thinking that they had obtained
        their goal, they weighed anchor and sailed along Crete, hugging the coast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But soon afterward a violent wind, called Euraquilo [a northeaster,
        a tempestuous windstorm like a typhoon], came rushing down from the island; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and when the ship was caught in it and could not head against the
        wind [to gain stability], we gave up and [letting her drift] were driven
        along. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "We ran under the shelter of a small island [twenty-five miles south
        of Crete] called Clauda, and with great difficulty we were able to get the
        ship\u2019s  skiff on the deck and secure it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "After hoisting the skiff [on board], they used support lines [for
        frapping] to undergird and brace the ship\u2019s hull; and fearing that they
        might run aground on the shallows of Syrtis [off the north coast of Africa],
        they let down the sea anchor and lowered the sails and were driven along
        [backwards with the bow into the wind]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'On the next day, as we were being violently tossed about by the storm
        [and taking on water], they began to jettison the cargo; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and on the third day they threw the ship\u2019s tackle (spare lines,
        blocks, miscellaneous equipment) overboard with their own hands [to further
        reduce the weight]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Since neither sun nor stars appeared for many days, and no small
        storm kept raging about us, from then on all hope of our being saved was
        [growing worse and worse and] gradually abandoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After they had gone a long time without food [because of seasickness
        and stress], Paul stood up before them and said, \u201CMen, you should have
        followed my advice and should not have set sail from Crete, and brought on
        this damage and loss. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But even now I urge you to keep up your courage and be in good spirits,
        because there will be no loss of life among you, but only loss of the ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For this very night an angel of the God to whom I belong and whom
        I serve stood before me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and said, \u2018Stop being afraid, Paul. You must stand before Caesar;
        and behold, God has given you [the lives of] all those who are sailing with
        you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So keep up your courage, men, for I believe God and have complete
        confidence in Him that it will turn out exactly as I have been told; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "but we must run [the ship] aground on some island.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The fourteenth night had come and we were drifting and being driven
        about in the Adriatic Sea, when about midnight the sailors began to suspect
        that they were approaching some land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So they took soundings [using a weighted line] and found [the depth
        to be] twenty fathoms (120 feet); and a little farther on they sounded again
        and found [the depth to be] fifteen fathoms (90 feet). '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then fearing that we might run aground somewhere on the rocks, they
        dropped four anchors from the stern [to slow the ship] and kept wishing for
        daybreak to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But as the sailors were trying to escape [secretly] from the ship
        and had let down the skiff into the sea, pretending that they were going
        to lay out anchors from the bow, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, \u201CUnless these men
        remain on the ship, you cannot be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then the soldiers cut away the ropes that held the skiff and let
        it fall and drift away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "While they waited for the day to dawn, Paul encouraged them all [and
        told them] to have some food, saying, \u201CThis is the fourteenth day that
        you have been constantly on watch and going without food, having eaten nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So I urge you to eat some food, for this is for your survival; for
        not a hair from the head of any of you will perish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Having said this, he took bread and gave thanks to God in front of
        them all, and he broke it and began to eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then all of them were encouraged and their spirits improved, and
        they also ate some food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'All told there were two hundred and seventy-six of us aboard the
        ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'After they had eaten enough, they began to lighten the ship by throwing
        the wheat [from Egypt] overboard into the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'When day came, they did not recognize the land, but they noticed
        a bay with a beach, and they decided to run the ship ashore there if they
        could. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So they cut the cables and severed the anchors and left them in the
        sea while at the same time unlashing the ropes of the rudders; and after
        hoisting the foresail to the wind, they headed steadily for the beach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'But striking a reef with waves breaking in on either side, they ran
        the ship aground. The prow (forward point) stuck fast and remained immovable,
        while the stern began to break up under the [violent] force of the waves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "The soldiers\u2019 plan was to kill the prisoners, so that none of
        them would dive overboard and swim [to land] and escape; "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'but the centurion, wanting to save Paul, kept them from [carrying
        out] their plan. He commanded those who could swim to jump overboard first
        and get to the shore; '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: and [he commanded] the rest to follow, some on [floating] planks,
        and others on various things from the ship. And so it was that all of them
        were brought safely to land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Safe at Malta'
      title: Safe at Malta
      number: 1
      content: '  After we were safe [on land], we found out that the island was
        called Malta. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the natives showed us extraordinary kindness and hospitality;
        for they kindled a fire and welcomed us all, since it had begun to rain and
        was cold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks and laid them on the
        fire, a viper crawled out because of the heat and fastened itself on his
        hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the natives saw the creature hanging from his hand, they began
        saying to one another, \u201CUndoubtedly this man is a murderer, and though
        he has been saved from the sea, Justice [the avenging goddess] has not permitted
        him to live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Paul [simply] shook the creature off into the fire and suffered
        no ill effects. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But they stood watching and expecting him to swell up or suddenly
        drop dead. But after they had waited a long time and had seen nothing unusual
        happen to him, they changed their minds and began saying that he was a god.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the vicinity of that place there were estates belonging to the
        leading man of the island, named Publius, who welcomed and entertained us
        hospitably for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened that the father of Publius was sick [in bed] with
        recurring attacks of fever and dysentery; and Paul went to him, and after
        he had prayed, he laid his hands on him and healed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After this occurred, the rest of the people on the island who had
        diseases were coming to him and being healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Paul Arrives at Rome'
      title: Paul Arrives at Rome
      number: 10
      content: 'They also gave us many honors [gifts and courtesies expressing respect];
        and when we were setting sail, they supplied us with all the things we needed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'At the end of three months we set sail on a ship which had wintered
        at the island, an Alexandrian ship with the Twin Brothers [Castor and Pollux]
        as its figurehead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'We landed at Syracuse [on Sicily] and stayed there three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "From there we sailed around and arrived at Rhegium [on Italy\u2019s
        southern tip]; and a day later a south wind came up, and on the second day
        we arrived at Puteoli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There we found some believers and were invited to stay with them
        for seven days. And so we came to Rome. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the brothers and sisters, having heard news about us, came from
        as far away as the Forum of Appius and Three Inns to meet us. When Paul saw
        them, he thanked God and was encouraged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When we entered Rome, Paul was allowed to stay by himself [in rented
        quarters] with the soldier who was guarding him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Three days later he called together the leaders of the Jews; and
        when they had gathered, he said to them, \u201CKinsmen, though I have done
        nothing against our people or against the customs of our fathers, yet I was
        turned over as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After they had interrogated me, they were ready to release me because
        I was not guilty of any offense deserving death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when the Jews objected [to my release], I was forced to appeal
        to Caesar (Emperor Nero), not because I had any charge to make against my
        nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For this reason I have asked to see you and talk with you, since
        it is for the sake of the hope of Israel (the Messiah, the resurrection)
        that I am bound with this chain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They said to him, \u201CWe have not received [any] letters about
        you from Judea, nor have any of the [Jewish] brothers come here and reported
        or said anything bad about you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But we would like to hear from you what your views are [that is,
        exactly what you believe]; for in regard to this sect (Christianity), we
        are fully aware that it is denounced everywhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When they had set a day for Paul, they came to his lodging in large
        numbers. And he carefully explained [Christianity] to them from morning until
        evening, solemnly testifying about the kingdom of God and trying to persuade
        them concerning Jesus, both from the Law of Moses and from the [writings
        of the] Prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Some were persuaded by what he said, but others would not believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They disagreed among themselves and they began to leave after Paul
        had made one last statement: \u201CThe Holy Spirit rightly spoke through
        Isaiah the prophet to your fathers, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018Go to this people and say,\u201CYou will keep on hearing, but
        will not understand,You will keep on seeing, but will not perceive;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For the heart (the understanding, the soul) of this people has become
        dull (calloused),And with their ears they scarcely hear,And they have shut
        their eyes [to the truth];Otherwise they might see with their eyes,And hear
        with their ears,And understand with their heart and return [to Me],And I
        would heal them.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore let it be known to you that [this message of] the salvation
        of God has been sent to the Gentiles; they indeed will listen!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '[And when he had said these things, the Jews left, arguing among
        themselves.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Paul lived there for two full years [at his own expense] in his
        own rented lodging and welcomed all who came to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: preaching and proclaiming the kingdom of God and teaching about the
        Lord Jesus Christ with all openness and boldness, unhindered and unrestrained.
      comments: []
